Commentary.Commentary: We are back for the final session of the day as the umpires are already out in the middle. The South African players are in a huddle as David Warner and Usman Khawaja make their way out to open the inning for Australia. Kagiso Rabada will begin proceedings with the new ball and he is raring to go. Let's play...
... DAY 1, SESSION 3 ...

Right then, we will return shortly for the third and final session of Day 1 and it will be the Australian openers who will walk out to bat and look to get their team off to a solid start. They are in a good position to bat the visitors out of this contest but they will be up against some quality fast bowling. South Africa need to come out with their tails up and look to do what the Australians did well and if they get some early wickets they will be right back in this game. Join us at 10.50 am IST (5.20 am GMT) to see how the hosts perform with the bat.

The Proteas came out looking to be watchful and negotiate the new ball but they lost their skipper, Dean Elgar, early and Rassie van der Dussen followed soon after. Sarel Erwee and Khaya Zondo were dismissed in the very next over with three wickets falling while the scoreboard read 27. Temba Bavuma and Kyle Verreynne began to rebuild the innings and put together a 98-run partnership in 141 balls as they looked to be positive. The wicket of Temba Bavuma on 38 initiated a collapse as they lost 6 wickets for 27 runs. Kyle Verreynne looked good as he played a counterattacking inning scoring 64 runs but his dismissal confirmed the demise of the South African inning.

The Australian fast bowlers were on the mark early after winning the toss and electing to bowl first, with Mitchell Starc and  Pat Cummins picking up a wicket each in their opening spell. Scott Boland was brought into the attack thereafter and he proved once again why he is so highly rated as he picked up two wickets in one over to have the opponents in serious trouble. There were unable to take a wicket up until Lunch and for a while after they returned but their patience finally bore fruit when Mitchell Starc got them the breakthrough. The wicket helped Nathan Lyon to run through the tail as he claimed 3 wickets for just 14 runs. Mitchell Starc also got three wickets and is one short of 300 Test wickets while Pat Cummins and Scott Boland chipped in with two wickets each.

South Africa have been bowled out in just 48.2 overs at the stroke of Tea! What an outstanding bowling display this has been from the hosts as they find themselves right on top of this Test match having restricted the Proteas to a first-inning total of 152 runs. They started really strong and had their opponents on the back foot from the word go and have pressed forward their advantage in a convincing manner. The visitors will be really disappointed with their lack of application on a wicket that had a little bit of help for the bowlers, but not enough for them to be bowled out in such a manner. They will now be chasing the game and have lots of work to do if they are to claw their way back into the contest.

OUT! CAUGHT! Pat Cummins picks up the final wicket of the innings here. It is a short ball, on fourth stump. Lungi Ngidi stay back, opens the face late and hits it straight to the man at gully. Cameron Green there takes a sharp catch to put South Africa out of their misery. The Proteas end their innings at 152/10.
Commentary.Howout: c Cameron Green b Pat Cummins

Commentary.Commentary: This is a length ball, on off. Lungi Ngidi blocks it back to the bowler.
Flatter, on off, blocked to covers.
A single now as this is knocked down to long on.

It is overpitched, on off. Kagiso Rabada comes down the track and throws his blade at it. The ball goes high in the air towards mid on. Mitchell Starc puts in a valiant effort but in vain. The batters take three.
On off, defended out.

It is tossed up, full and on middle. Kagiso Rabada gets low and tries to go for the reverse sweep. Does not connect though and gets pinged on his pads. Lyon appeals and the finger goes up. Kagiso Rabada is quick to take the review. The original decision had to be overturned as Rabada got a glove on it.
Quicker and full, on off, driven back to the bowler.
JAFFA! It is a length ball, in the channel. Lungi Ngidi tries to block it away but does so inside the line.
A sharp bouncer, on leg. Rabada ducks under it.
A good-length ball, outside off, shaping away from the batter. Ngidi tries to chase it but gets beaten in the process.

What is this bounce? It is a length ball, in-line with the stumps. Lungi Ngidi gives himself a bit of room as he tries to carve it through the off side. The ball though spits off the deck which gets the better of Lungi Ngidi.
Lungi Ngidi blocks this full delivery with a straight bat to extra covers.
Back of a length, on middle. Rabada pulls it to deep square leg for one.
Pat Cummins (11-3-34-1) brings himself back into the attack.
So close! This is looped up, outside off. It grips and turns in a bit late. Lungi Ngidi premeditate the leave and is fortunate enough to not see the stumps get shattered.
It is tossed up, full and on off. Lungi Ngidi gets on his front foot and gets it past slip fielder. The batters pick a couple.
Around off, defended out.
It is full, on middle and leg. Ngidi flicks it aerially to mid-wicket.
This is outside off. It grips and turns in. Ngidi gets a blow on his pads.
Lungi Ngidi is the last man in.

OUT! CAUGHT! Nathan Lyon strikes once again and he is getting some vicious turn here on Day 1! Bowls this slightly short and well outside off, gets the ball to turn in sharply off the wicket. Anrich Nortje gets his front foot forward and looks to defend this. He does not expect the ball to bounce as much and it catches his gloves and lobs up to the right of the pitch. Travis Head at silly point dives forward and grabs hold of the ball. There is a huge appeal but Anrich Nortje has already turned and begun walking towards the dressing room. South Africa are nine down now and in an absolute mess.
Commentary.Howout: c Travis Head b Nathan Lyon

Commentary.Commentary: Good length, angling down leg. Kagiso Rabada tries to help it around the corner but misses. A probing over from Starc comes to an end.
FOUR! Top class! It is very full, wide of off. Kagiso Rabada leans in and drives it through the gap at covers. He times it to perfection and finds the boundary.
This is a length ball, sliding down leg. Kagiso Rabada looks to clip it away but misses.

A bouncer now over middle. Kagiso Rabada shuffles and tries to pull it away but misses. Alex Carey gathers the ball and thinks he has got his man. Mitchell Starc signals that he did not hear anything. Carey though convinces the skipper and takes the review for caught behind. The Snicko later confirms that there is no bat on it. The final decision is NOT OUT. Australia lose a review here.
JAFFA! It is on a length, around off. It flies off the deck with some away movement. Kagiso Rabada looks to chase it but misses.
A good-length ball, on fourth stump. Kagiso Rabada dabs it with soft hands to Smith at second slip. Does not carry.
Goes full again, on off. Anrich Nortje gets on his front foot and blocks it into the deck.
On off, defended out.
Slower through the air, on off. Nortje blocks it to silly point.
This is looped up, on off. Nortje strides forward and blocks it to point off the outer half.
Full again, on off. Anrich Nortje presses forward and blocks it back to the bowler.
Tossed up and full, on off. Anrich Nortje defends it on his front foot.
Starc fires in a yorker, right in the blockhole. Kagiso Rabada digs it out back to the bowler.
Length, on off, blocked back to the bowler.
Fuller, on middle and leg. Kagiso Rabada flicks it to mid on.

DROPPED! A tough chance nonetheless. It is a short ball, on the bodyline. Kagiso Rabada gets inside the line and tucks it to the man at short leg. Travis Head fails to grab it at he first go, he gets a couple more chances but spills it in the end.
Very full and straight on the pads. Rabada stays back and flicks it to mid-wicket. Pat Cummins misfields there and the batters take two.
Back of a length, wide of off. Kagiso Rabada plays it late to the right of gully. Green is quick to get low to his right and gather the ball.
Anrich Nortje is the number 10 batter and he makes his way out to the crease.

OUT! CAUGHT AT SLIP! The resistance of Kyle Verreynne comes to an end. Nathan Lyon picks up his second wicket and he is delighted about the same. It is looped up, on off. It grips and turns away a touch. Kyle Verreynne shuffles and looks to defend it out. The ball takes a thick outside edge and goes to first slip. Steven Smith stationed there takes a dolly. South Africa are falling apart here.
Commentary.Howout: c Steven Smith b Nathan Lyon

Commentary.Commentary: On off, blocked out.

FOUR BYES! Sharp turn and bounce. This is tossed up, on off. It grips and turns away down leg a long way. Kyle Verreynne misses his flick. The ball goes past the keeper and has enough legs to reach the boundary at fine leg.
Floats it up, on off. Kyle Verreynne gets across and tucks it to short mid-wicket.
Around middle and leg, nudged to mid-wicket.
Flatter, on off. Kyle Verreynne blocks it out.
Kagiso Rabada walks out to middle.

OUT! CAUGHT AT SLIPS! Mitchell Starc picks up his 299th wicket in Test cricket. Starc comes from 'round the wicket and angles a length ball into the batter. It nips away a touch off the deck. Keshav Maharaj tries to flirt with it but only manages to get a thick outside edge. Steven Smith in the slip cordon makes no mistake.
Commentary.Howout: c Steven Smith b Mitchell Starc

Commentary.Commentary: A sharp bouncer, on leg stump. Keshav Maharaj ducks under it.
Very full, outside off. Keshav Maharaj guides it past gully and comes back for two runs.
On a length, wide of off. Keshav Maharaj looks to chase it but misses.
Much fuller, attacking the stumps from 'round the wicket. Keshav Maharaj blocks it back to the bowler.
A length ball, too straight on the pads, Kyle Verreynne stays back and flicks it in front of square on the leg side for a single.
Bowls this slower in the air and outside off on a fuller length. Keshav Maharaj blocks this towards point.
Keshav Maharaj is the new man at the crease.

OUT! CAUGHT! What has Marco Jansen done? He has thrown his wicket away when his team needed him to hang in there! Nathan Lyon flights this one full and outside off. Marco Jansen decides to go after the bowling and shimmies down the wicket to get to the pitch of the ball. He takes a wild swing but does not connect cleanly and the ball takes the outside half of the bat to go high into the air. Cameron Green at mid-wicket has to run back but keeps his eyes firmly on the ball. Takes a wonderful catch facing the boundary and South Africa have lost their sixth wicket. Irresponsible batting from the young fast bowler especially with Kyle Verreynne looking good on the other end.
Commentary.Howout: c Cameron Green b Nathan Lyon

Commentary.Commentary: Loopy delivery bowled full and just outside off. Marco Jansen defends this back down the pitch towards the bowler.
It is tossed up, on off, turns into the batter. Kyle Verreynne flicks it to square leg and crosses.
On off, blocked out.
Nathan Lyon floats this one full and outside off. Kyle Verreynne goes deep in the crease and blocks this to the off side.
Decides to go 'round the wicket for the last ball and serves this really full, outside off. Marco Jansen digs this out towards cover.
Goes back to bowling on a good length and outside the off stump. Marco Jansen leaves this one alone as well.
Bangs this in short and in line with the stumps. Marco Jansen does well to duck under this one and let it through to the keeper.
Angles this one away from the batter on a good length and outside off. Marco Jansen opts to leave this one alone.
Bowls this one back of a length and outside off. Marco Jansen looks to hit this on the up and gets beaten on the outside edge.
Mitchell Starc bowls this on a good length and into the pads. Kyle Verreynne clips this to the right of mid-wicket and takes a single.

Loopy delivery bowled full and outside the off stump. Marco Jansen gets a good stride forward and gets beaten by the spin as the ball raps against the pads. A stifled appeal from the players around the bat.
Bowls this one short and spinning down leg. Marco Jansen does not offer a shot and it goes off his pads into the hands of square leg.
Bowls this full once again and outside the off pole. Marco Jansen uses his feet as well and knocks this straight to mid off.
Flights this one full and outside off, Kyle Verreynne shimmies down the wicket and eases tis down to long on for a single
Goes full this and serves this outside the off stump. Kyle Verreynne goes on the backfoot and blocks this back down the pitch.
Nathan Lyon bowls this short and outside off, Kyle Verreynne rocks back and flicks this towards mid-wicket.

Drinks break! The Proteas have fought well so far in the post-Lunch session. The stand between Temba Bavuma and Kyle Verreynne really helped their side to get back on track, although the former could not continue till the end of this session. Australia might feel that they have an opening here and would look to pounce on this opportunity and get into the tail as soon as possible.
Attacks this stumps on a good length. Marco Jansen is watchful as he defends this solidly towards mid-wicket.
On a good length this time and fractionally outside off. Kyle Verreynne attempts to block but gets an inside edge that goes towards deep backward square leg for a single.
Goes over the wicket to Kyle Verreynne and bowls this full, outside off. Kyle Verreynne dabs this towards the gully fielder.
Bowls this slightly fuller and outside the off stump. Marco Jansen taps this towards cover-point and takes a single.
A touch wider but still on a good length. Marco Jansen opts to leave this one alone.
Mitchell Starc bowls from 'round the wicket and serves this on a good length outside off. Marcus Harris blocks this towards cover.
Bowls this into the pads on a shorter length, Kyle Verreynne rocks back and flicks this onto the square leg fielder.
Loopy delivery bowled full and outside off. Marco Jansen gets a stride forward and looks to block. Gets a thick outside edge towards backward point and they take a single.
Angles this into the stumps on a fuller length. Marco Jansen pushes this towards short mid on.
Bowls this one slightly short and into the pads. Kyle Verreynne tucks this to deep square leg and takes a single.
Flights this one full and outside off. Kyle Verreynne shimmied down the wicket and clips the ball straight to short mid-wicket.
Nathan Lyon starts with a fullish delivery outside the off stump. Kyle Verreynne blocks this watchfully towards the off side.
Starc comes 'round the wicket for the final delivery. He serves it on a length, outside off, coming in with the angle. Jansen watches it sail past him and into the keeper's mitts.
A short ball, angling across the right-hander. Jansen leaves it alone for the keeper.
Starc goes full, attacking the off pole. Jansen blocks it into the deck.
Marco Jansen strides out to the middle and South Africa will have to rebuild once again.

OUT! DRAGGED ON! Mitchell Starc gets his second wicket and breaks this gritty stand on 98 runs. Starc serves a full ball, around off. This one nips in a touch. Temba Bavuma gets on his front foot and tries to defend it out but plays the wrong line. The ball takes an inside edge and goes on to rattle the stumps. Now, half of the South Africa side is back in the pavilion.
Commentary.Howout: b Mitchell Starc

Commentary.Commentary: Short again, wide of off. Temba Bavuma stays back and cuts it hard to deep point. Nathan Lyon cuts it out in the deep and keeps it down to a couple. The stand moves to 98.
Back of a length, on the bodyline. Temba Bavuma tries to flick it to the leg side but it hits him on his hand and goes back to the bowler.
This full delivery is driven to mid off. The batters take a single.
Good length, shaping in from outside off. Temba Bavuma shuffles and leaves it alone.
WIDE! A sharp bouncer, on off. This one flies over the batter's head and the umpire signals a wide.
Outside off, left alone.
On a length, outside off, it shapes in a touch while also staying low off the deck. Kyle Verreynne defends it awkwardly to point and rotates the strike.
It is fuller, outside off. Temba Bavuma leans in and drives it through the gap at covers. The batters take three before Marnus Labuschagne cuts it out.
Slightly short, wide of off. Temba Bavuma lets it be.
Good length, on middle. Kyle Verreynne blocks it to the right of the bowler.
Shorter, on fourth stump, shaping away. Kyle Verreynne shuffles and shoulders his arms at it.
Quicker and fuller, on leg. Bavuma eases it towards mid on and scampers across for a quick single. The stand moves to 90 now.
A short ball this time, angled across the right-hander. Temba Bavuma has no shot to offer.
Length, on off, defended out.

FOUR! This is a good-looking shot. Temba Bavuma is finding his feet here. It is a length ball, angled across the right-hander. Temba Bavuma hit it on the up and creams it through covers for a boundary.
Shorter, wide of off. Kyle Verreynne shoulders his arms at it.
This is a full-length delivery, at 136 clicks. It jags back in from outside off and hits Kyle Verreynne on his thigh pads.
A length ball, straying on the pads, Kyle Verreynne flicks it to mid-wicket.
This one is outside off. Kyle Verreynne leaves it alone.
On off, blocked out.
FOUR! Nicely played. It is overpitched, wide of off. Kyle Verreynne steps forwards and drives it through the gap at backward point for a boundary.

A loud appeal for lbw but turned down! Cummins dishes a full delivery, on middle and leg. Temba Bavuma misses his flick and gets rapped on his pads. It seems to be going down leg and the umpire keeps his finger low. Pat Cummins has a chat with Alex Carey but does not opt for the review. The replays later confirm that the ball is missing the wickets. A good decision by Australia for not taking the review.
Kyle Verreynne flicks it off his pads to square leg for a single. The stand moves to 81.
Slightly short, close to off. Kyle Verreynne hops and taps it to point.
A peach of a delivery! Good length, on fifth stump, this one hold its line. Kyle Verreynne tries to chase it but misses.
Much fuller, on off. Kyle Verreynne gets forward and digs it back to the bowler.

FOUR! Kyle Verreynne gets his half-century in fine fashion. He would know that the job is still half done, but this is what his side needed. It is short, on off. Kyle Verreynne swivels and pulls it over mid-wicket for a boundary.
A touch wider outside off and on a good length. Temba Bavuma is happy to leave this one alone as well.
Continues bowling on a good length and outside off. Temba Bavuma shoulders his arms to this one.
Bowls this on a good length and on an off stump line. Kyle Verreynne punches this straight to the left of mid on and they take a single.
Attempts a yorker but serves this really full just outside off. Kyle Verreynne gets his bat down in time and gets an inside edge onto his pads.

Goes full this time and wide outside off, Temba Bavuma goes after this one and lofts it over cover for three runs as Marnus Labuschagne gives chase once again. That brings up the 100 for South Africa and this has been a good recovery from them.

What a beauty of a delivery! Scott Boland still getting the ball to move about nicely here. Bowls this on a good length and angles this into the batter from outside off. Temba Bavuma looks to play for the line but the ball moves away a fraction after pitching. Gets beaten all ends up.
Pulls his length back a fraction and serves this into the pads. Temba Bavuma goes deep in the crease and tucks this towards square leg.
Delivers this on a good length and straight at the stumps. Temba Bavuma defends this back towards the bowler.
Goes short this time and in line with the stumps. Kyle Verreynne gets on top of the bounce and pulls this towards deep backward square leg for a single.
Bowls this back of a length and outside off. Kyle Verreynne stands tall and punches the ball towards point.
Bowls this one on a good length and outside off. Kyle Verreynne gets his front foot forward and blocks the ball towards cover.

FOUR! This has been swatted away to the fence! Pat Cummins bowls this short and wide outside off. Kyle Verreynne goes hard at the ball with no intention to keep it down. Gets this towards the deep backward point fence for four runs.
Another full delivery this time outside off. Kyle Verreynne shuffles across and clips the ball to the right of mid on for a single to retain strike.
Decides to go full once again and fires this into the stumps. Kyle Verreynne is watchful and blocks this back towards the bowler.
Pulls his length back and bowls this short, outside off. Kyle Verreynne cuts this straight to the point fielder.
Goes slightly fuller and just outside the off pole. Kyle Verreynne pushes this towards mid on.
This is on a good length and aimed for the stumps. Kyle Verreynne blocks this towards mid-wicket.
Scott Boland bowls this on a fuller length and outside off. Kyle Verreynne taps this tentatively to the left of the bowler.
Pat Cummins serves this one outside off on a good length. Temba Bavuma taps this towards gully.
This is on a good length and angled into the stumps. Temba Bavuma clips this towards deep backward square leg and takes a couple of runs.
Another full delivery wide outside off. Kyle Verreynne strokes this towards deep backward point and they take three runs as the fielder gives chase.
Bowls this a fraction fuller and outside off, Kyle Verreynne pushes forward to block but gets an inside edge towards mid-wicket.
Bowls this on a good length and just outside off. The ball nips back in sharply and Kyle Verreynne trusts the bounce as he lets it go through to the keeper. The ball goes just over the stumps.
Pat Cummins begins with a delivery bowled back of a length and in line with the stumps. Kyle Verreynne gets on his toes and blocks the ball to the leg side.
Pat Cummins to bowl from the other end.
Gets this one to nip back in from a fuller length. Temba Bavuma judges this outside off stump line well and leaves the ball alone.
Wider outside off on a fuller length. Temba Bavuma reaches for the ball and taps it to the gully fielder.
Continues bowling full and a touch closer to the stumps outside off. Temba Bavuma gets his front foot forward and shoulders arms.
Goes a touch fuller this time but still outside the off pole. Temba Bavuma continues to let the ball go through to the keeper.
Bowls this back of a length and outside off, Temba Bavuma gets on his toes and leaves this one alone.

Scott Boland starts off with a full delivery outside the off stump. Kyle Verreynne leans into the drive and beats the diving Marnus Labuschagne at cover. He gets up to give chase and the batters take three runs.

We are back for the second session on Day 1 as the umpires stride out to the middle. The Australian players are in a huddle at the boundary line as Temba Bavuma and Kyle Verreynne make their way out to continue their partnership. The Aussies take up their fielding positions on the field and it will be Scott Boland to begin proceedings after the break. Let's go...
... DAY 1, SESSION 2 ...

Australia are in the driving seat here and will surely come out with all guns blazing to break this gritty stand for the fifth wicket. Will they be able to get an early breakthrough? Or will Temba Bavuma and Kyle Verreynne continue with their fightback? Do join us at 8.30 am IST (3 am GMT) to find out how things pan out.

Scott Boland is up for a chat and he says that they will take this score at lunch and feels that they bowled well. Mentions that after winning the toss, they got a chance to bowl and they did well to get the four wickets. Claims that he is happy with any wicket he gets.

This was the greenest of pitches ever seen at the Gabba. Keeping the conditions in mind, Pat Cummins won the toss and opted to bowl first. Everyone was surprised at first but the decision started paying dividends straightaway due to Australia's threatening seam attack. Scott Boland had an instant impact with the ball in hand, as he took two wickets in just his second over of the innings to put South Africa in a spot of bother.

After being put to bat, South Africa were unable to find their rhythm with the blade. The Proteas lost their skipper quite early on. But it got even worse for them, when they lost three more wickets with 27 runs on the board. The seamers did come to the party and took apart the top-order in a jiffy. Kyle Verreynne and Temba Bavuma hold the key for the visitors. The two have stitched together a stand of 57 runs so far and would be surely eyeing to remain unscathed in the post-Lunch session.

So, the morning session on Day 1 truly belonged to Australia. They receive a warm ovation as they make their way to the dressing room. The Proteas surely have their task cut out. They need something special from here, if they are to crawl back in this match.
Goes 'round the wicket for the last ball of the morning session. Bowls this one on a good length and outside off. Temba Bavuma shoulders his arms to this one as well. That will be LUNCH on Day 1.
Bowls this one slightly wider outside off on a fuller length. Temba Bavuma does not get tempted into playing this and leaves it alone.
On a good length and just outside off. Temba Bavuma happy to leave this one alone.
Continues bowling full and this time on the pads. Temba Bavuma blocks this to the right of the bowler.

Mitchell Starc goes full this time and bowls this outside off. Kyle Verreynne reaches for this and knocks this towards deep cover-point. Marnus Labuschagne gives chase and once again puts and outstanding dive to keep the ball from reaching the ropes. The batters complete three runs.
Bowls this on a good length and on a leg stump line. Temba Bavuma clears his front foot and taps this towards cover for a quick single.
Angles this one into the stumps on a fuller length. Kyle Verreynne clips this towards mid-wicket and ends the over with a dot ball.
Flights this one a bit and bowls this full, in line with the stumps. Kyle Verreynne blocks this back down the pitch towards the bowler.
Bowls this slightly short and angled into the pads. Kyle Verreynne clips this towards the short leg fielder. He had a chance but the ball came far too quickly.
FOUR! That is a great release shot and Kyle Verreynne not allowing the bowler to settle. Nathan Lyon goes full and outside off, Kyle Verreynne reverse sweeps this towards third man for four runs.
Floats this one fuller and outside the off stump. Kyle Verreynne gets across to the off side and blocks the ball towards cover.
Nathan Lyon begins with a short ball outside the off pole that goes straight through. Kyle Verreynne leaves this one alone.

FOUR! Another lucky boundary as South Africa keep the scoreboard ticking! Mitchell Starc bowls this full and outside off. Temba Bavuma looks to drive and gets an outside edge that goes in the gap in the slip cordon for four runs to third man.
This is on a good length as well and outside off. Temba Bavuma initially looks to play at this and decides against it at the last moment.
Back to bowling on a good length and close to the off pole. Temba Bavuma judges the line well and lets it go through to the keeper.
Goes fuller this time and wide outside the off stump. Temba Bavuma reaches for it and knocks this through cover-point for a couple of runs.
On a good length once again and outside off, Temba Bavuma looks to play at this and gets a bottom edge that goes on the bounce to second slip.
Mitchell Starc angles this away from the right-hander on a good length, well outside off. Temba Bavuma lets this one go through to the keeper.
A touch fuller this time but still outside the off stump. Kyle Verreynne defends this towards mid off.
Continues bowling on a good length and outside off. Kyle Verreynne decides to leave this one alone.
This is on a good length as well and outside off. Kyle Verreynne gets across t9o the off side and tucks this towards mid-wicket.
Bowls this on a good length and outside off. Kyle Verreynne blocks this solidly towards mid off.

FOUR! Streaky boundary but they all count! Pat Cummins continues bowling full and outside off. Kyle Verreynne looks to drive and gets a thick outside edge that flies in the gap between third slip and gully for four runs.
Pat Cummins goes full and just outside the off stump. Temba Bavuma works this to the right of mid on and takes a single.

FOUR! Runs coming at a steady pace now for South Africa! Mitchell Starc bowls this on a good length and in line with the stumps. Kyle Verreynne gets across the line of the ball and flicks this towards fine leg for four runs.
Goes really full this time but angling down leg. Kyle Verreynne looks to flick this fine but misses as it goes through to the keeper.
Bowls this one slightly back of a length and outside off. Kyle Verreynne stands tall and blocks the ball towards gully.
Bowls this on a good length and angling away from outside off. Kyle Verreynne shoulders his arms to this one.

That was close! Mitchell Starc continues bowling on a good length and attacks the pads. Kyle Verreynne flicks this to the right of square leg and looks for a run. Temba Bavuma sends him back and he slips as he turns. Travis Head picks up the ball and takes aim at the striker's end but misses. Direct hit and Kyle Verreynne was a goner.
Mitchell Starc starts off with a good length delivery on a leg stump line. Kyle Verreynne clips this straight to the square leg fielder.
Goes a fraction fuller this time and outside off. Kyle Verreynne looks to block but gets an inside edge to the right of mid-wicket and they take a run.
Continues bowling on a good length and in line with the stumps. Temba Bavuma clips this towards mid-wicket and takes a single.
Bowls this on a good length and outside the off pole. Temba Bavuma is watchful this time and raises his arms to leave the ball alone.
Beaten! Continues bowling back of a length and just outside off. Temba Bavuma feels for this one and the ball goes past his outside edge.
FOUR! That has been punched away! Pat Cummins bowls this slightly short and close to the off stump. Temba Bavuma gets on his backfoot and thumps this towards deep point for a cracking boundary.
Pat Cummins begins his second spell with a back-of-a-length delivery outside off. Temba Bavuma is not interested in playing at this.
A dot to end the over! It is full, around off. Kyle Verreynne pats it back to the bowler. Just a single off the over then.
Length, on middle. Bavuma shuffles and flicks it to square leg for a single.
This one is swinging in from outside off. Temba Bavuma blocks it to the off side.
Full, on fifth stump. Left alone.
Length again, outside off, jags back in off the deck. Temba Bavuma takes a blow on his thigh pads.
An inswinging delivery, full and on off. Bavuma defends it into covers off his front foot.
FOUR! Nicely played! It is on a length, wide of off. Kyle Verreynne stays back, opens the face late and steers it down to third man. It races away to the fence.
A sharp bouncer, on off. Kyle Verreynne sways away from the line of the delivery.
Good length, on off. Kyle Verreynne pushes it to point. Marnus Labuschagne slides, turns and throws it wayward which results in an overthrow. They take two.
Much fuller, on off. Bavuma gets on his front foot and guides it through the gap at point for a single.
Back of a length, on off, tapped to covers.
Good length, on fourth stump, with some extra bounce. Bavuma gets it to gully off the outer half.
Bowls this on a good length and outside the off pole. Kyle Verreynne stands tall and raises his arms high as he leaves the ball alone.
Decides to go full once again and on an off stump line. Temba Bavuma works this to in the gap at cover and takes one.
Delivers this one back of a length and outside off. Temba Bavuma shoulders his arms and leaves the ball alone.
Goes full once again and well outside off. Temba Bavuma punches this towards point.
Bowls this one on a good length and outside off. Kyle Verreynne taps this towards cover and takes a quick run.
Scott Boland bowls this full and outside the off stump. Temba Bavuma gets a stride forward and knocks the ball to the left of mid off for a single.
Delivers this on a good length and just outside the off pole. Kyle Verreynne blocks this solidly into the off side.
Angles this into the pads on a good length. Temba Bavuma looks to work this leg side but misses and the ball goes off the pads towards square leg. They take a leg bye.
This is wide outside off on a shorter length. Temba Bavuma does not offer any shot.
Bowls this on a good length and in line with the stumps. Kyle Verreynne clips this towards deep square leg and looks for two. He slips at the non-striker's end and they have to settle for a single.
Bangs this in short and angling down leg. Kyle Verreynne looks to pull this but misses and Alex Carey collects this to his left.
Cameron Green begins with a good length delivery outside off. Temba Bavuma taps this towards cover-point and takes a quick run.
Good length, outside off. Shaping in late. Kyle Verreynne lets it be. A probing over from Boland comes to an end.
Continues bowling full and outside off, Kyle Verreynne pushes at this and gets and outside edge that falls just short of the third slip fielder.
Goes slightly full and outside off, Kyle Verreynne knocks this straight to mid off.
Bowls this one back of a length and angled into the batter. Kyle Verreynne gets beaten on the inside edge as the ball come in sharply.
Good-length delivery bowled outside the off stump. Temba Bavuma taps this towards point and takes a quick single.
Scott Boland bowls this on a good length and outside off, Temba Bavuma chooses to leave this one alone.
On a fuller length, on off pole. Kyle Verreynne tries to chase it but misses.
On off, blocked out.
SIX! Wonderfully played! It is a short ball, wide of off. Kyle Verreynne stays back and slashes. It goes all the way over the point fence.
Fuller, on leg, clipped to short mid-wicket.
FOUR! Kyle Verreynne gets his first boundary. It is a short ball, outside off. Kyle Verreynne stands tall, rides the bounce well and pulls it over mid-wicket for a boundary.
Green starts with a loosener. Quite full, down leg. Bavuma clips it to deep square leg and rotates the strike.
Cameron Green has been brought into the attack.
So it is a maiden for Boland. Good length, on top of off. Kyle Verreynne stays back and blocks it solidly to covers.
Good delivery! On a length, outside off, it jags back in off the deck. Kyle Verreynne gets an inside edge onto his pads.
Very full, on fifth stump. Kyle Verreynne strides across and lets it be.
This is much fuller, angled into the pads. Kyle Verreynne closes the face and works it to the left of mid on.
An inswinger this time, full and on off. Kyle Verreynne gets on his front foot and drives it to covers.
Fuller, on middle and leg. Kyle Verreynne knocks it to mid on.
Touch fuller, on off. Bavuma steers it to the man at gully.
A single now as this is pushed to covers. Kyle Verreynne is off the mark now.
On a good length this time and just outside off. Kyle Verreynne tucks this towards short mid on.

Lucky! It could've been worse for the Proteas. It is a length ball, on off. Bavuma opens the face and guides it towards backward point. Green is quick to get to ball as he tries to restrict a single here. Kyle Verreynne is long way down the middle but Green throws it at the wrong end. In the end, South Africa get a single through overthrow.
A length ball, pitching outside off, jags back in a bit. Temba Bavuma gets it to the off side off the outer half.
Full length, wide of off, left alone.
Kyle Verreynne is the new batter out in the middle with South Africa in all sorts of trouble.

OUT! LBW! Scott Boland appeals for lbw and the finger goes up in a flash. Khaya Zondo though takes the review. Coming to the delivery, it is on a length, outside off, shaping in off the deck. Khaya Zondo is caught insde his crease. He tries to block it away but misses and takes a blow high on his pads. The on-field umpire thinks Boland has got his man here. The Snicko later confirms that no bat is involved. The Ball Tracking shows that it is umpire's call on the ball hitting the wickets. Hence the on-field decision stands but South Africa do not lose their review, unlike their batter.
Commentary.Howout: lbw b Scott Boland

Commentary.Commentary: A length ball, coming in from outside off. Zondo hangs back and defends it to covers. No is the call straightaway.

DRINKS! The umpires have decided to take a refreshment break. South Africa are in all sorts of trouble as they have lost their top three batters in the first hour itself and have loads of work to do if they are to claw their way back into this game. Australia will be thrilled with their decision at the toss as their three fast bowlers have all chipped in with one wicket each. Khaya Zondo has made his way out to the middle and he will have to build a partnership with Temba Bavuma.

OUT! CAUGHT AT GULLY! The crowd at the Gabba is on its feet here. This is exceptional bowling from the hosts and South Africa lose their third wicket inside the first hour of the morning session. Bolan dishes it full, on fourth stump. Sarel Erwee tries to drive it through covers but gets a thick outside the edge. The ball stays very low and goes to the left of gully. Cameron Green keeps his eyes on the ball, get low down to his left in a flash and gathers the ball with both hands to begin the celebration.
Commentary.Howout: c Cameron Green b Scott Boland

Commentary.Commentary: Good length, on fourth stump, extracts some extra bounce. Sarel Erwee shoulders his arms at it.
Two dots on the trot! Overpitched once again, outside off. Sarel Erwee watches the ball sail past him.
Boland goes full, wide outside off. Sarel Erwee lets it be.
Back of a length this time and outside off, Temba Bavuma goes on his backfoot and looks to fend this away. Gets beaten all ends up.
Goes fuller this time and outside the off stump. Temba Bavuma mistimes his drive straight to the short cover fielder.
Bangs this in slightly short in line with the stumps, Temba Bavuma looks to defend but gets squared up and the ball comes off his gloves to hit his body.
Bowls this one closer to the stumps on a good length. Temba Bavuma eases this towards short mid on.
Another lovely delivery first up to Temba Bavuma! Bowls this slightly full and outside off. Temba Bavuma looks to defend on his backfoot and gets beaten on the outside edge.
Temba Bavuma is the new man in.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Australia have their second and their decision to bowl first is paying dividends! Pat Cummins claims his first wicket and Rassie van der Dussen's short stay at the wicket comes to an end. This is bowled on a good length and just outside the off stump. Rassie van der Dussen looks to push at the ball and decides against it at the last moment. The ball takes a faint knick and goes through to the keeper. Alex Carey takes a regulation catch and South Africa are two down inside the first 10 overs.
Commentary.Howout: c Alex Carey b Pat Cummins

Commentary.Commentary: What a jaffa to end the over! Bowls this one on a good length and outside off stump. Sarel Erwee feels for this one but is nowhere near the ball.
This is full as well and close to the off pole. Sarel Erwee blocks this firmly towards short mid off.
Another dull delivery outside the off stump, Sarel Erwee reaches for it and slices it towards backward point.
FOUR! Sarel Erwee gets his second boundary! Scott Boland continues bowling full and just outside the off pole. Sarel Erwee strokes this towards long off and gets four more runs.
Goes 'round the wicket now to the southpaw and bowls this full, attacking the stumps. Sarel Erwee clips this towards mid-wicket.

Scott Boland is right on the money straightaway! Bowls this one full and angling into the stumps from just outside off. Rassie van der Dussen looks to block but gets an inside edge towards backward square leg and they take a single.
Change. Scott Boland comes into the attack now.

FOUR! That is the first time the ball goes beyond the boundary line! Pat Cummins goes 'round the wicket and bowls this full, into the stumps. Sarel Erwee punches this with a straight bat down to long on for a lovely boundary.
Keeps bowling on a good length but this is bowled in line with the stumps. Sarel Erwee strokes this straight to short mid on.
Continues bowling on a good length and pitching on an off stump line. Sarel Erwee makes a really good leave as the ball swings away from the off pole and misses it by a fraction.
On a good length this time but still outside the off stump. Sarel Erwee knocks this towards mid off.
Bowls this one back of a length and outside the off pole. Sarel Erwee stands tall and looks to play at this but gets beaten by the lateral movement away from the bat.
Pat Cummins decides to go over the wicket to the left-hander this time and bowls this on a good length, outside off. Sarel Erwee is solid in defense as he blocks this towards cover.
Bowls this on a good length and outside the off stump. Rassie van der Dussen shoulders his arms to this one as well.
Continues bowling full and outside the off pole. Rassie van der Dussen chooses to leaves this one alone.

FOUR RUNS! Great timing from Rassie van der Dussen! Mitchell Starc bowls this full and outside the off stump. Rassie van der Dussen gets his front foot forward and leans into the shot. He knocks this towards deep cover and Marnus Labuschagne gives chase. He does well to stop the ball from getting to the ropes but the batters run four irrespective.
Delivers this one slightly short as well and angled into leg. Sarel Erwee goes on the back foot and tucks this to the left of mid-wicket for a single.
Bowls this one back of a length and just outside off, Sarel Erwee gets on his toes and blocks this ball towards cover.
Mitchell Starc bowls this on a fuller length and angled into the stumps. Sarel Erwee knocks this towards mid on.

That's a beauty from Pat Cummins! Bowls this on a good length and just outside the off pole. Gets the ball to move away slightly and beats the outside edge of Rassie van der Dussen's bat as he hangs it out to dry.

Goes over the wicket to the right-hander and bowls this on a good length outside off. Rassie van der Dussen gets squared up as he looks to block and gets the ball towards point from the outside half of his bat.
Sarel Erwee is off the mark after facing 18 dot balls. Pat Cummins bowls this on a good length and outside the off stump. Sarel Erwee taps this towards cover and takes a quick single.
Pulls his length back slightly and gets it into the batter from outside off, Sarel Erwee judges the line well and leaves the ball alone.
Bowls this one on a good length as well and outside off, gets this one to move away from the left-hander. Sarel Erwee feels for the ball and gets beaten all ends up.

Pat Cummins continues from 'round the wicket and serves this on a good length, just outside off. The ball nips back in sharply and there is some extra bounce off the surface. Sarel Erwee looks to fend but gets an inside edge into his groin area.
Goes full, angling across the right-hander. Rassie van der Dussen strides forward and shoulders his arms at it. A good leave to end the over. A wicket-maiden for the left-handed seamer now.
A sharp bouncer, on off. Rassie van der Dussen lets it be.
This is much fuller, on off, swinging back in late. Rassie van der Dussen closes the face and nudges it to mid-wicket.
Outside off, no shot to offer yet again.
This is very full, angled across the right-hander, close to the tramline. Left alone.
Rassie van der Dussen makes his way out to the middle at number 3.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Australia strike early and they will surely be happy to see the back of Dean Elgar right away as he walks back on just three runs. The ploy of going down leg finally does the trick for the hosts. This is a good-length ball, angling down leg. It extracts some extra bounce off the deck as well. Dean Elgar hangs back and tries to flick it away. The ball takes the inside edge and flies to the right of the keeper. Alex Carey dives to that side and takes a stunning catch.
Commentary.Howout: c Alex Carey b Mitchell Starc

Commentary.Commentary: Good length, wide of off, shaping in late. Erwee covers his stumps and lets it be. A second maiden for Cummins here.
This one comes in with the angle, on a length from outside off. Sarel Erwee tries to leave it alone but takes a blow high on his pads. No appeal made as it looks quite high.
On off, blocked out.
Good carry! Back of a length, wide of off, shaping away this time. Sarel Erwee keeps his blade to himself.
Good length, on fourth stump, seaming in late. Sarel Erwee shoulders his arms at it.
This is angled in, full and on off. Erwee opens the face and guides it to Lyon at point.
Fuller, on fourth stump. Elgar taps it to point but straight to the fielder.
A low full toss bowled outside the off stump. Dean Elgar works this to deep point and takes a couple of runs.
This is on a length, angling down leg. Dean Elgar looks to play it around the corner but misses.
It is full, on middle. Elgar flicks it to mid on.

NOT OUT! The ball has not touched the bat at all and the onfield decision stays. It is an outswinging delivery, full and outside off. Dean Elgar tries to drive it away but does not connect and the ball goes under the bat. The ball seems to have it a footmark as it deviates after bouncing beyond the bat before it goes to the keeper but the slip cordon thinks it is an edge. The on-field umpire does not raise his finger but walks over to his colleague to check if there is a bump ball. They take it upstairs and give not out as the soft-signal. The replays later confirm the decision. Dean Elgar extends his stay at the crease.

The umpires have gone upstairs to check for a bump ball. The soft signal is not out and replays show that the ball seems to have gone below the bat. Hotspot confirms that the ball has missed the bat as it grazes against the floor.
This is much quicker, on a length, angling down leg. Dean Elgar stays back and looks to nudge it away but misses.
Four dots on the trot to end the over! It is slightly short, wide of off. Sarel Erwee lets it sail past him.
This is on a good length, wide of off. Erwee has no shot to offer.
Very full, moving away. Erwee gets it to Lyon at point.
Outside off, left alone.

FOUR LEG BYES! A repeat dose! Cummins continues to come 'round the wicket. Goes down leg once again. Erwee gets inside the line but misses his clip. It brushes his pads and races away to the fine leg fence.
FOUR LEG BYES! A length ball, sliding down leg. Sarel Erwee gets caught on his thigh pad as he fails to glance it around the corner. Nonetheless, it races away to the fine leg fence.
Pat Cummins the captain of Australia has decided to share the attack and bowl from the other end.

LEG BYE! A yorker-length delivery, angling down leg. Sarel Erwee tries to flick it away but misses and slips on the ground. It goes to short fine off the pads. They collect a leg bye. This has been a tidy start for Australia.
Outside off, jagging away. Erwee leaves it alone.
Good length, around the hips. Erwee flicks it to the right of shrt midwicket. Travis Head dives to that side and makes a sharp stop.
Elgar and South Africa are off the mark. It is a length ball, sliding down leg. Dean Elgar hops and clips it to square leg. One taken.
Much fuller this time, on off. Elgar presses forward and defends it to covers.
Mitchell Starc starts with a length ball, around middle, shaping away from the batter. Dean Elgar squares up as he blocks it out awkwardly.

We are all set to commence this highly anticipated series. The umpires make their way out to the middle and the Australian players are in a huddle beyond the boundary line. They disperse to take their respective positions on the field as the South African openers stride out towards a really green looking pitch. Dean Elgar and Sarel Erwee will look to get their team off to a steady start but will be facing Mitchell Starc first up and he will begin proceedings with the new ball. Let's play...
Australia (Playing XI) - David Warner, Usman Khawaja, Marnus Labuschagne, Steven Smith, Travis Head, Cameron Green, Alex Carey (WK), Pat Cummins (C), Mitchell Starc, Nathan Lyon, Scott Boland.

South Africa (Playing XI) - Dean Elgar (C), Sarel Erwee, Rassie van der Dussen, Temba Bavuma, Khaya Zondo, Kyle Verreynne (WK), Marco Jansen, Keshav Maharaj, Kagiso Rabada, Anrich Nortje, Lungi Ngidi.
TOSS - The captains are out in the middle. The coin is flipped into the air and lands in favor of Australia. They have elected to BOWL first.

South Africa hold the second spot in the Test Championship standings but some unfavorable results in recent Test matches has them in a dogfight with Sri Lanka and India to maintain their position. A series loss could be catastrophic for them in the context of making it to the finale and will have to look back at their three consecutive series wins on Australian shores to gain confidence going into this game. They have had their issues finding consistency in their batting but their strong pace bowling unit could hold the key to unlocking a formidable Aussie side. Will the Proteas be able to start strong in their quest for the fourth consecutive away series win against the hosts? Or will Australia continue their dominance in the longest format of the game?  We will find out soon. Stay tuned for the toss and team updates.

Australia currently find themselves at the top of the Test Championship table and look most likely to reach the finals next year as they have a superior point percentage going into this game. They will be playing the two contenders for the final spots and a series win here against South Africa will guarantee their spot before they make a difficult trip to India to play their next series. They have a strong batting lineup that has been amazingly consistent this year and with the pitches most likely to aid the batters, we expect them to continue raking in the runs. They do have some injury concerns in their bowling department but hosts have never had a dearth of quality backup players on whom they can count.

Hello and a warm welcome, ladies and gentlemen to our coverage of the first Test match in the three-match series between Australia and South Africa at The Gabba in Brisbane as both teams are looking for a crucial win in a hunt for Test Championship points. This will be the first time these two teams lock horns since the scandal that hit the Australian side in the 2018 series. We are bound to witness a fiery encounter if there are any residual feelings left after the incident and even more so if you consider the fact that the hosts have not won a Test series against the Proteas on home soil since the 2005-06 Test series. There is a lot at stake as with anticipate a blockbuster contest between two heavyweights of the game.
... MATCH DAY ...

We are back for the third essay and Australia will look to build on this lead of 66 runs. The umpires and the Australian players are out on the field. Dean Elgar and Sarel Erwee will open the innings and will be hoping for a better start this time around. Mitchell Starc has been handed the new ball and will begin proceedings. Let's go...
... THIRD INNINGS ...

What a fantastic match of cricket this is turning out to be as South Africa have managed to bundle out the hosts for 218. The Aussies walk away with a handy lead of 66 runs. The Proteas would be really happy with the way they came back in this match. Australia started positively with the blade on Day 2 with Cameron Green joining the set batter Travis Head in the middle. Although, their happiness was cut short when Marco Jansen got rid of both batters in a single over. Later, Mitchell Starc and Alex Carey added some crucial runs to the tally but the South African seamers made sure to get rid of the tail as soon as possible without causing much damage. South Africa now will be coming out with an intent to build a huge mountain for the Aussies to climb. There is still a lot of time left in this Test match but the way the pitch is playing, this game can be concluded well before the scheduled time. Do join us shortly to find out how things pan out for South Africa with the bat for the second time in this match.

OUT! CAUGHT! Kagiso Rabada wraps up the Australian inning! Australia have a lead of 66 runs and South Africa will be thrilled with their effort this morning. Kagiso Rabada bowls this on a good length and just outside off. Nathan Lyon looks to play this leg side but gets a leading edge that lobs up over the bowler's head. Rassie van der Dussen is at mid off and he runs to his right before sliding and taking a lovely catch. Australia would have loved to increase their lead a bit more but any advantage on this pitch will be massively useful.
Commentary.Howout: c Rassie van der Dussen b Kagiso Rabada

Commentary.Commentary: This is on a good length and outside the off stump. Nathan Lyon is looking to play his shots and gets beaten on the outside edge.
Kagiso Rabada bowls this full and into the pads. Alex Carey clips this to deep square leg and takes one. He shows faith in Nathan Lyon by taking a single on the first delivery.
Lungi Ngidi goes full and just outside off, gets the ball to shape away a fraction. Nathan Lyon looks to drive but is beaten.
Bangs this in short and outside off. Alex Carey looks to upper cut this but does not time it well. Luckily for him, the ball lands just short of the incoming deep backward point fielder.
Goes full once again and attacks the stumps. Alex Carey defends this back towards the bowler.
Angles this into the stumps on a fuller length. Alex Carey flicks this towards mid-wicket.
Lungi Ngidi goes full this time and outside off, Alex Carey knocks this straight to the cover fielder.
Bowls this back of a length and into the pads. Alex Carey tucks this towards deep square leg and takes a couple of runs.
Bowls this on a good length and in line with the stumps. Nathan Lyon blocks this bakc down the pitch.

OUT! CAUGHT! Kagiso Rabada gets his third and Pat Cummins departs after being peppered with short balls! Kagiso Rabada goes a touch fuller this time and Pat Cummins looks to swing across the line of the ball. He mishits the ball and it goes high towards mid-wicket. Anrich Nortje takes a comfortable catch and Australia lose their ninth wicket. This dismissal is the result of the short balls earlier in the over.
Commentary.Howout: c Anrich Nortje b Kagiso Rabada

Commentary.Commentary: Short once again and in line with the stumps. Pat Cummins sways out of the way awkwardly.

Bangs this in short and into the batter. Pat Cummins ducks but keeps his arms up to fend off the ball. The ball gets the hands and goes to gully where Temba Bavuma takes an easy catch. The umpire raises his finger but Pat Cummins reviews immediately. replays show the ball has come off the arm guard.
This is in line with the stumps on a good length. Alex Carey clips this towards square leg and takes a single.
Bowls this on a good length and just outside off. Alex Carey punches this to the right of cover.

OUT! CAUGHT AND BOWLED! That is a wonderful catch by Lungi Ngidi on his follow-through! He bowls this one on a good length and in line with the stumps. Mitchell Starc looks to punch this straight but the ball seems to have got stuck in the pitch a bit. It lobs towards the bowler who has to go really low to take the catch inches off the ground. The bowling change works once again and Australia lose their eighth wicket. Pat Cummins walks out to the middle.
Commentary.Howout: c & b Lungi Ngidi

Commentary.Commentary: Angles this one down leg once again on a fuller length. Alex Carey clips this one wide of square leg for a single.
Strays onto the pads on a good length. Alex Carey tucks this toward deep square leg and they run really well to complete a couple of runs.
This is on a good length and outside off. Mitchell Starc taps this towards cover with soft hands and takes a single.
What a jaffa! Bowls this one angled into the stumps on a good length. The ball straightens after pitching and beats the outside edge of the bat as Mitchell Starc feels for this.

FOUR! Lungi Ngidi has been welcomed to the crease with a boundary! Goes full and in line with the stumps. Mitchell Starc hits this uppishly to the left of the bowler and the ball goes past the umpire for four runs.
Lungi Ngidi has been brought into the attack.
Bowls this one outside the off pole on a good length. Mitchell Starc knocks this through cover-point and takes an easy single.
Kagiso Rabada bangs this in short and outside off. Mitchell Starc fends this awkwardly towards gully.
NO BALL! Bowls this slightly fuller and outside off. Mitchell Starc miscues his shot towards mid on. He oversteps though and it will be a no ball.
Pulls his length back a fraction and serves this outside off. Mitchell Starc punches this towards backward point.
Continues to bowl on a good length and outside the off stump. Mitchell Starc knocks this straight to the mid off fielder once again.
Bowls this on a good length and just outside off. Mitchell Starc blocks this towards mid off.
Kagiso Rabada bowls this back of a length and on a leg stump line. Alex Carey clips this through mid-wicket and takes a single.

DRINKS! Australia started positively and scored freely but two quick wickets got the momentum back in the favor of South Africa. There is another partnership building here and the Proteas need to wrap up this innings at the earliest. Australia will be eager to build on this lead and put the pressure on the visitors.
Continues bowling on a good length and outside off. Mitchell Starc pushes at the ball and gets an outside edge that falls short of the slip fielder.
Bowls this on a good length and into the pads. Mitchell Starc dabs this to the leg side.
Marco Jansen goes 'round the wicket and bowls this short just outside off. Mitchell Starc keeps his bat down and lets the ball go through to the keeper.
Bowls this back of a length and angling down leg. Alex Carey tucks this into the square leg region and takes one.
Goes slightly full this time and angles this into the stumps. Alex Carey clips this through mid-wicket and picks up a couple of runs.
Marco Jansen bowls this on a good length and just outside the off pole. Alex Carey blocks this back towards the bowler.
Bangs this in short and into the batter. Mitchell Starc gets on his toes and fends the ball into the pitch.
Goes full and just outside off, Mitchell Starc gets on the front foot and defends this solidly.
Continues bowling outside off on a good length. Alex Carey taps this towards cover and takes a single.
This is on a good length as well and outside off. Alex Carey looks to block but gets an inside edge onto his elbow.
Bowls this one back of a length and into the batter. Alex Carey tucks this towards square leg.
Kagiso Rabada comes back into the attack and bowls this on a good length, into the stumps. Alex Carey smothers this into the pitch.
Back of a length this time and just outside off. The ball rises sharply and beats the outside edge of the bat.
Marco Jansen goes 'round the wicket now and serves this on a good length in line with the stumps. Mitchell Starc defends this back towards the bowler.
Delivers this wide outside off on a good length. Mitchell Starc leaves this one alone.
Strays onto the pads once again on a fuller length. Alex Carey clips this towards mid-wicket and takes a quick single.
Goes full once again and outside off. Alex Carey knocks this straight to mid off.
Bowls this on a fuller length and into the pads. Alex Carey looks to work this leg side but gets a leading edge down the pitch.
FOUR! That has been swatted away! Anrich Nortje continues bowling short and outside off. This one sits up nicely for Mitchell Starc as he pulls it towards deep mid-wicket for his second boundary.
Bowls this back of a length as well and gets it to nip back in from outside off. Mitchell Starc judges the line well and leaves the ball alone.
Pulls his length back a fraction but serves this well outside the off stump. Mitchell Starc happy to let this go through to the keeper.
Goes full this time and angles this into the stumps. Mitchell Starc mishits his heave towards mid on.
This is bowled back of a length and outside the off pole. Mitchell Starc shoulders his arms to this one.
Anrich Nortje begins from 'round the wicket and bowls this on a good length, outside off. Alex Carey knocks this to deep cover-point and takes a run.
Bowls this on a good length as well and outside off. Mitchell Starc hangs his bat out to dry and gets beaten all ends up.
On a good length and outside off. Mitchell Starc raises his arms and leaves this one alone.
Delivers this on a good length as well and outside the off stump. Alex Carey punches this to deep backward point and takes a single.
Bowls this outside off on a good length. Alex Carey pushes at this and gets an outside edge to gully.
FOUR RUNS! This is short as well and into the batter, Alex Carey pulls this towards deep square leg and the fielder gives chase. He cuts it off but the batters run four runs.
Marco Jansen bangs this in short and going down leg. Alex Carey looks to pull but misses.
Bowls this one back of a length and outside off, Mitchell Starc goes on the back foot and defends this solidly.
Bowls this full and outside off, Mitchell Starc mishits the ball straight to mid off.
Bowls this back of a length and outside off, Mitchell Starc opts to leave this one alone.
Bowls this into the stumps in a fuller length. Alex Carey tucks this towards mid-wicket with soft hands and takes quick single.
On a good length once again and straight. Alex Carey taps this to the left of the bowler.
Beaten! Anrich Nortje goes 'round the wicket and bowls this on a good length and outside off. Alex Carey feels for the ball and is beaten.
FOUR! Mitchell Starc is off the mark in typical style! Marco Jansen goes full and outside the off stump. Mitchell Starc lofts this over the infield and gets a boundary to long off.
On a good length and into the stumps, Mitchell Starc eases this towards mid on.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Marco Jansen has two wickets in the over and he has claimed the big wicket of Travis Head! There will be two new batters at the crease now and South Africa may sense that they could bowl out the hosts soon. This is bowled back of a length and angling down leg. Travis Head looks to tuck this down leg side but gets a slight tickle off the gloves and goes into Kyle Verreynne's gloves. There is a massive appeal and the umpire raises his finger. Travis Head discusses this with his partner and decides to review it. Hotspot shows no signs of any glove on the ball but Snicko has a murmur when the ball and the gloves are next to each other. The onfield decision stays, Australia loose their seventh wicket and also lose a review. Travis Head falls short of yet another hundred and Mitchell Starc makes his way out to the middle.
Commentary.Howout: c Kyle Verreynne b Marco Jansen

Commentary.Commentary: Bowls this one on a good length and just outside off, Alex Carey taps the ball towards cover and takes a quick single to get off the mark.

OUT! CAUGHT! South Africa have their first wicket of the morning, and Marco Jansen strikes straight away! He serves this full and outside the off pole, the angle taking the ball away from the batter. Cameron Green goes for the expansive drive and gets a thick outside edge that flies towards third slip. Keshav Maharaj is unable to hold onto the ball on his left and the ball loops into the air. Sarel Erwee at first slip runs for the rebound and takes a catch diving forward. Australia lose their sixth wicket and after a brisk start, South Africa finally have a breakthrough. Alex Carey is the new batter who walks out to the middle.
Commentary.Howout: c Sarel Erwee b Marco Jansen

Commentary.Commentary: Marco Jansen starts with a good-length delivery angled into the pads. Travis Head goes deep in the crease and flicks this towards deep mid-wicket for three runs.
Marco Jansen has been brought into the attack.
Beaten! Bowls this slightly back of a length and outside off. Cameron Green pushes at the line of the ball and gets beaten all ends up.
Bowls this one on a good length and outside off. Cameron Green looks to punch this through the offside but gets an inside edge onto his legs.
Outside the off pole once again and on a good length. Cameron Green defends this solidly to the left of the bowler once again.
Pulls his length back slightly and serves this outside the off pole. Cameron Green decides to leave this one alone.
Bowls this on a good length and outside off. Cameron Green blocks this to the left of the bowler.

FOUR! Australia have come out looking positive and have been scoring freely this morning! Anrich Nortje bowls this on a good length but strays onto the pads. Cameron Green clips thos to deep square leg for another four runs.
Bowls this back of a length and into the body. Cameron Green tucks this into the leg side and takes a quick single as Kagiso Rabada runs to his right to collect the ball.

FOUR! Cameron Green is picking Kagiso Rabada off here! The bowler goes full once again outside the off pole. Cameron Green gets a stride forward and thumps this down to long off once again for another boundary.
Pulls his length back a fraction and serves this outside off. Cameron Green taps this towards point.
Bowls this on a good length and angles this in from outside off. Cameron Green blocks this towards cover.
Bowls this one back of a length and outside off. Travis Head punches this to deep cover and takes three runs. Brings up 2000 runs for Travis Head in Test cricket.
Kagiso Rabada comes 'round the wicket now to the southpaw and starts off with a short ball angled into the batter. Travis Head ducks under this one.
Bowls this one short and outside off. Travis Head cuts this hard to deep backward point and takes a single to keep strike.
Goes full this time and in line with the stumps. Travis Head flicks this towards deep mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
Beaten! On a good length and outside off, gets some extra bounce off the surface. Travis Head feels for the ball and it beats his outside edge.
This is on a good length and outside off, Travis Head punches this to deep backward point and takes a couple of runs.

FOUR LEG BYES! A cry of frustration from the bowled as he strays down leg side on a slightly shorter length. Travis Head looks to tuck this fine but misses and the ball goes off the thigh pads for four leg byes to fine leg.
Anrich Nortje starts off with a back-of-a-length delivery just outside off. Travis Head gets on his toes and fends the ball to the off side.
Bowls this one on a good length once again. Cameron Green blocks this watchfully towards cover.
FOUR! This is poor bowling from Kagiso Rabada! He serves this full and just outside off. Cameron Green strokes this straight to long off for an easy boundary.
Delivers this on a good length and outside off, Cameron Green defends this solidly towards cover.
Full once again and just outside the off stump. Cameron Green gets squared up a bit and the ball takes the outside half of the bat and goes towards gully.
Goes a touch fuller and outside the off pole. Cameron Green knocks this firmly towards short mid off.
Better start to this over from Kagiso Rabada. Bowls this one on a good length and outside the off stump. Cameron Green raises his arms and leaves this one alone.
Maiden to start for Anrich Nortje. Bowls this one on a good length and angling away from the batter. Travis Head feels for this and gets beaten on the outside edge.
Goes back to bowling on a good length and outside off. Travis Head taps this towards the gully fielder.
Delivers this one back of a length and outside the off stump. Travis Head fends this towards backward point and looks for a single. Cameron Green refuses.
This is in line with the stumps on a good length. Travis Head knocks this to the left of bowler.
Bowls this on a good length and outside the off pole. Travis Head blocks this towards short mid off.
Anrich Nortje bowls this on a good length but strays down leg. Travis Head looks to flick but misses.
Anrich Nortje will bowl from the other end.

FOUR! What a way to get your first boundary! Kagiso Rabada bowls this full and outside off. Cameron Green punches this to long off for four runs. Great start for Australia and should help settle any nerves on a new day. Australia have the lead now.
Bowls this one short and outside off, Travis Head gets on top of the bounce and cuts this towards deep point for three runs.
This is fuller and still outside off. Travis Head finds the cover fielder once again.
Goes full from 'round the wicket to the left-hander and serves this outside off. Travis Head knocks this straight to cover.
Kagiso Rabada starts the day with a full delivery straying on the pads. Cameron Green eases this to the left of mid-wicket and takes a single to get off the mark straightaway.

We are all set for the game to resume on Day 2. The umpires are out in the middle as the South African players enter the field and form a huddle. They disperse and take their respective positions in the field while Travis Head is joined by Cameron Green after the loss of a wicket on the last ball of the day. Kagiso Rabada  will begin proceedings with the ball as he is set to complete his over. Let's play...

The South African seamers made the most of the assistance available on this deck. Keshav Maharaj has been expensive and took a massive beating but would hope some cracks open up as the game progresses. Both teams would be looking for a solid start in the morning session to get a slight advantage. Which team will be able to grab this game by the scruff of the neck? Stick around to find out.

Australia are still trailing by 7 runs but have 5 wickets left in hand with Travis Head unbeaten on 78 in just 77 deliveries. He looks pretty set at the crease and has racked up runs for fun on Day 1 with his counterattacking cricket. He will certainly be key to this Australian inning and his performance along with the tail wagging should set up a good first-inning lead for the hosts.

Hello and a warm welcome, ladies and gentlemen to our coverage of Day 2 of the first Test match in the three-match series between Australia and South Africa at The Gabba in Brisbane The crowd at the Gabba has been treated to some enticing cricket on Day 1 and would be hoping for something similar this time around as well.
... DAY 2, SESSION 1 ...

Right then. That's it from Day 1. Australia still trail by 7 runs but now just have 5 wickets left in hand. The morning session on Day 2 will be very crucial and would provide us with a more clear picture as to which side has the upper hand. The first ball will be at 5.50 am IST (12.20 am GMT) on 18th December, but as you all know you can join us early for the build-up. Cheers!

South Africa surely deserves a pat on the back for a remarkable performance. One would've thought it to be a walk in the park for Australia to cut down the deficit of 152 runs but it turned out to be an enticing affair. The Proteas' seamers caused a lot of problems to the top order. They kept asking the right questions and got rid of the top three in a blink of an eye. South Africa later lost some control as they were unable to maintain good lines and lengths. Eventually, at the cusp of Stumps, Anrich Nortje and Kagiso Rabada provided a wicket each to send half of the Australian side back into the pavilion.

This has been some great counterattacking cricket by the hosts! Australia were in all sorts of trouble when they lost their top three batters cheaply. At one stage they were teetering at 27/3 inside 10 overs. Not the start they would've envisioned for themselves. One would have thought that Australia could find it difficult to put a fightback from an early setback but Smith and Head surely had other ideas. Travis Head started his innings cautiously but once he got his eye in, there was no stopping him. He raced away to 78 off 77 balls, while Smith enjoyed playing the second-fiddle. They stitched together a stand of 117 runs before Smith slipped up. Scott Boland came in as the nightwatchman to play a couple of remaining overs but he couldn't control his itch and ended up nicking one behind to conclude the day.

Oh boy! What an entertaining Day 1 of a Test match this turned out to be. We saw a total of 15 wickets fall throughout the day. This game is surely moving at a rapid pace. The Proteas started their day on the back foot but have managed to crawl back into the match with an influential outing with the ball in hand.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! South Africa have ended this session strongly and are back in this game which has swung like a pendulum. Kagiso Rabada gets an extended spell and is asked to ball the last over before Stumps and he delivers. He serves this on a good length and outside the off stump. Scott Boland gets forward to block this but the ball deviates slightly after pitching. Takes a faint outside edge as it goes through to Kyle Verreynne behind the wicket and Australia have lost half their side. The umpires have decided to call for Stumps and South Africa head to the dressing room with a spring in their step.
Commentary.Howout: c Kyle Verreynne b Kagiso Rabada

Commentary.Commentary: On a good length and just outside off. Travis Head blocks this solidly to end the penultimate over before stumps with a dot ball.
A length ball, around the hips. Boland flicks it to square leg for one. He gets off strike and the crowd gives him a massive cheer.
This has taken off the surface! Nasty delivery as it is bowled back of a length and outside off. Scott Boland fends it awkwardly towards point.
Bangs this in short a way outside the off stump. Scott Boland swings hard at the ball but misses. Is he a night watchman or a pinch hitter?
Scott Boland is the new batter in.

OUT! TIMBER! Anrich Nortje gets the breakthrough and it is the big wicket of Steven Smith! This late wicket gives South Africa the momentum just before stumps and they will be pumped. Anrich Nortje bowls this on a good length and outside the off pole. Gets the ball to nip back into the batter and Steven Smith gets his bat down late. The ball goes through his defenses and shatters the stumps. Australia lose their fourth wicket and they would have preferred to end the day with the partnership intact.
Commentary.Howout: b Anrich Nortje

Commentary.Commentary: Anrich Nortje bowls this on a good length and just outside off. Steven Smith defends this back towards the bowler.
Goes back to bowling back of a length and outside off. Travis Head raises his arms and leaves this one alone.
Full and straying into the pads, Travis Head clips ths ball towards deep mid-wicket and picks up a brace.
Bowls this slightly back of a length and it comes back into the batter from outside off. Travis Head gets an inside edge into his pads and the ball lands in front on the keeper.
FOUR! That has been crunched away! Kagiso Rabada goes full this time outside off, from 'round the wicket. Travis Head knocks this towards long off and collects a boundary.
Bowls this on a good length as well and outside off, gets this one to come back in. Steven Smith gets beaten by the extra bounce and the inside edge goes towards square leg for a single.

What a beauty from Kagiso Rabada as he still getting the ball to nip in the 7th over of his spell. Bowls this on a good length and just outside off. Steven Smith feels for this and gets beaten all ends up.
Bowls this on a good length pitching outside leg. Travis Head looks to work this leg side but gets cramped for room. Gets hit on the inside part of his leg and he says ouch!
Continues to bowl on a good length and angles this into the stumps. Steven Smith clips this into the vacant mid-wicket region and takes one.
Bowls this on a good length and outside the off stump. Steven Smith continues to be watchful and leaves the ball alone.
Pulls his length back aa fraction and serves this just outside the off pole. Steven Smith judges this well and raises his arms at the last moment.
On a good length this time and outside the off stump. Steven Smith taps this towards point.
Bowls this back of a length and just outside off. Steven Smith gets behind the line of the ball and blocks this back towards the bowler.
FOUR! A boundary to end the over. Slightly short, outside off. Head goes back and steers it through the gap at slip cordon. The ball has enough legs to reach the fence.
A sharp bouncer, on middle. Head ducks under it without any hesitation.
Travis Head stays back to this length delivery and fends it out to covers.
This is a length ball, on off. Head plays it back to the bowler.
On a length, on off. Head pushes it to cover.
A short ball, just on top of off. Travis Head decides to duck under it but leaves his blade above his head. Kyle Verreynne gathers and thinks the batter has got some glove on it.
On a good length once again and outside the off stump. Steven Smith raises his arms high into the air and leaves three in a row.
Goes slightly fuller but bowls on the same line. Steven Smith continues to shoulder arms.
Bowls this one back of a length and outside off, Steven Smith is happy to leave this one alone.
A low full toss bowled just outside the off stump. Travis Head miscues his shot wide of mid on and takes a single.

FOUR! Travis Head continues his attacking approach! Anrich Nortje bangs this in short and wide outside off. Travis Head gets high on his toes and cuts this over the infield towards the deep backward point fence for four runs.
Anrich Nortje goes full and angles this in from outside off. Travis Head looks to clip this leg side but gets a leading edge to cover.
This is bowled back of a length and outside off. Steven Smith gets up on his toes and fends the ball down into the pitch.
Bowls this wide outside off on a good length. Steven Smith leaves this one alone.
Goes back to bowling on a good length and outside off. Steven Smith is well behind this one as he defends it back to the bowler.
100-run partnership in just 110 balls! Kagiso Rabada bowls this full and into the pads. Travis Head clips this towards deep mid-wicket for a single.
On a good length and outside the off stump. Travis Head blocks this back towards the bowler.
Edged and falls safe! Kagiso Rabada goes 'round the wicket and bowls this just outside off. Travis Head feels for this and gets an outside edge that falls short of second slip
Continues bowling on a good length and outside the off stump. Steven Smith shimmies down the wicket across the stumps and leaves it alone at the last moment.
On a good length once again and outside off. Steven Smith blocks this solidly towards mid off.
That inside edge seems to have got Steven Smith's focus back! This is bowled on a good length and outside off. Steven Smith leaves this one alone and lets it go through to the keeper.
Bowls this slightly back of a length and outside the off stump. Steven Smith pushes at this and gets an inside edge close to the stumps.
A low full toss bowled outside the off pole. Steven Smith punches this towards point and Keshav Maharaj puts in a good dive to his right and half-stops the ball. The batters take two runs though.
