Lungi Ngidi bowls this on a good length and outside the off pole. Steven Smith leaves this one alone.
Bowls this on a good length and outside the off stump. Travis Head gets into position to cut this but gets beaten.
FOUR! That has been timed to perfection! Kagiso Rabada goes full and offers width outside off, Travis Head gets forward and strokes this towards long off for four runs.
Pulls his length back once again and serves this outside off. Travis Head punches this off his back foot towards cover.
Goes full this time and angles this into the stumps. Travis Head clips this towards mid on.
Bowls this one back of a length as well and outside off. Travis Head looks to cut but mistimes his shot to the right of the bowler.
Kagiso Rabada bowls this back of a length and angled into the batter. Travis Head gets on his toes and blocks this back towards mid on.
This is outside off, Smith has nothing to offer.
Touch fuller, on off. Smith dries it down the ground. Lungi Ngidi dives to his right and gets a hand on it. He certainly saves a boundary here.
Slightly short, outside off. Smith leaves it alone for the keeper.
A single now as this is flicked past mid on.
A legth ball, angled into the batter. Head is not left with much room and he blocks it with straight bat.
Shorter, going down leg. Smith swivels and pulls it to fine leg for a single.
Head remains inside the crease to block this length ball.
Short ball, on middle. Smith pull it to deep mid-wicket and crosses.
Fuller, angled into the batter. Smith clips it towards mid on.
Length and on fourth stump. This one flies off the deck. Steven Smith gets squared up a bit. He gets it to point off the outer half.
It is full, on off pole. Steven Smith drives it down to long on for a couple.
On off, defended out.

FOUR! Not a great over by Lungi Ngidi. 15 runs come off the over. It is a good-length ball, angled down leg. Head hangs back and glances it down to fine leg for four runs. Australia seem to be in a hurry to cut down the deficit here. They are just 37 runs behind now.
Length, on off. Head defends it out with full face.

SIX! ALL THE WAY! Travis Head racks up his half-century is less than a run a ball. He is turning the game on its head here. It is full, angling down leg. Head stands back and flicks it powerfully over the square leg fence for a maximum.
FOUR! Head is oozing with confidence now. It is very full, wide of off. Head leans in and crunches it through covers for a boundary.
A length ball, on top of off. Head blocks it out with closed bat.
Smith helps it around the corner and crosses for a single.

FOUR! Incredible shot! Back of a length, on off. Head stands tall and pulls it over mid-wicket. The ball races towards the boundary ropes. Head goes into his 40s, while Australia have 100 on the board now.
Short ball, angled down leg. Smith drags his pull to fine leg and rotates the strike.
It is full in length, angling down leg. Head stays back and wrists it towards cow corner. Temba Bavuma gives it a chase and keeps it down to three runs.
On off, blocked to covers. Three dots on the trot.
Rabada goes full and on off. Head defends it into the deck on the front foot.
Length, around off. Head defends it out to safety.
A short ball, on off. Head stays back and punches it through cover-point. The batters take three before the fielder cuts it out.
FOUR! Great shot! Head has his eye-in now. It is looped up, full and outside off. Head gets low and smashes it through covers for a fine boundary.
Smith flicks this full delivery to mid-wicket. They take a single as Rassie van der Dussen makes a half stop.
Full and in-line with the stumps. Smith eases it back to the bowler.
On off, defended out.
Floated and full, outside off. Smith gets forward and defends it out.
Continues to bowl outside off on a good length. Travis Head pushes this firmly towards cover.
Pulls his length back a fraction and serves this outside off. Travis Head uses the crease and blocks this back towards the bowler.

FOUR! Runs are flowing thick and fast now for Australia! Kagiso Rabada goes really full and in line with the stumps. Travis Head flicks this aerially towards deep mid-wicket for the second boundary of the over.
Strays onto the pads on a good length. Steven Smith flicks this down to fine leg for a single.

FOUR! That is a really good-looking shot from Steven Smith! Kagiso Rabada goes full and offers width outside off. Steven Smith leans into the shot and creams this to deep cover for beautiful boundary. Brings up the 50-run partnership between these two.
Kagiso Rabada starts with a short ball outside off. Travis Head mistimes his shot wide of mid off and they take a run.
Goes full once again and strays onto the pads. Travis Head clips this towards deep square leg for a single.
Keshav Maharaj bowls this quick and full, just outside off. Travis Head goes back in the crease and blocks this towards mid-wicket.
FOUR! Short once again and gets the treatment! Khaya Zondo bowls this just outside off, Travis Head makes room and cuts this to deep cover for the second boundary in the over.
Flights this one full and outside the off stump. Travis Head strokes this firmly to mid off.
FOUR! Travis Head gets this one away nicely! Keshav Maharaj is quite short and angles this down leg. Travis Head forces this down to fine leg and collects four runs.
Keshav Maharaj begins with a full delivery served outside off. Travis Head gets forward and defends this solidly.
Continues bowling on a good length and in line with the stumps. Steven Smith blocks this to the right of the bowler.
Bowls this on a good length and outside off, Steven Smith leaves this one alone.
Another short ball that does not rise much. Bowls this in line with the stumps, Steven Smith looks to pull but misses and gets hit on the groin.

FOUR! What sublime timing from Steven Smith! Anrich Nortje bowls this on a fuller length and just outside the off stump. Steven Smith shows the straight face of the bat and punches this down to long on for four more runs.
Bowls this one on a good length and outside off, Steven Smith gets across the line and blocks this to the left of the bowler.

FOUR! Steven Smith gets hold of this one and dispatches it to the boundary! Anrich Nortje bangs this in short and outside off, the ball does not rise as much as he expected it to. Steven Smith gets on top of this and pulls this towards deep square leg for four runs.
On a good length and in line with the stumps. Travis Head blocks this back towards the bowler.
Bowls this on a good length and outside the off pole. Travis Head looks to cut this but the ball is not short enough and gets beaten under his bat.
Goes fuller time and outside off, Travis Head strokes this firmly to the left of short cover. The fielder dives in that direction and stops the ball.
Almost chops this back onto the stumps! Marco Jansen bowls this on a good length and gets the ball to nip back in. Travis Head looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto his pads.
Bowls this one back of a length and outside the off pole. Travis Head raises his arms and lets it go through to the keeper.
FOUR! Picked off the pads in style! Marco Jansen goes full and angles this down leg. Travis Head keeps his head still and clips this to deep mid-wicket for a lovely boundary.
This is outside the off stump on a fuller length. Travis Head digs this out towards cover and takes a quick run.
Bowls this on a good length and outside the off stump. Steven Smith taps this with soft hands towards cover and takes a single.
Goes full this time and on an off stump line. Travis Head flicks this through the mid-wicket region and they run well to take three runs.
Continues bowling on a good length and just outside off. Travis Head taps this towards point.
Bowls this on a good length and outside off, Steven Smith knocks this to the right of point and a good stop by the fielder restricts them to a single.
Anrich Nortje bowls this back of a length and angling into the pads from 'round the wicket. Travis Head clips this down to fine leg for a single.

DRINKS! The players will take some refreshments and South Africa would have loved this period of play after the Tea break. They have managed to make a mark on this game courtesy of their bowlers and will be looking to get a few more wickets before Stumps. Australia started off in the worst manner losing David Warner on the very first delivery and soon their other opener and the in-form Marnus Labuschagne found themselves back in the dressing room. Steven Smith and Travis Head will look to build a partnership here and begin rebuilding the innings.
Touch shorter, this one climbs on the batters. Smith nudges it to short leg.
Length, on off. Smith shuffes and flicks it to mid-wicket.
This is a length ball, pitching outside off and coming into the batter with the angle. Smith works it to the leg side.
This is way fuller, attacking the blockhole, coming in with the arm. Smith digs it out in time.
Jansen continues to come 'round the wicket. This is a length ball, angled into the batter but far enough for him to bother him.
Outside off, left alone.
A short ball, on the pads. Head gets pinged on his thigh pads.
FOUR! This should boost his confidence. It is slightly short, outside off. Travis Head gets on his toes and punches it through point for a boundary.
Touch short, on the hips. Smith clips it past short leg and collects a single.
Nortje angles in a short ball, on off. It shapes away a touch in the end. Smith slashes and misses.

BYE! Cuts the batter in half. Nortje steams in and serves a length ball, on off. This one stays very low off the deck. Head stays back and tries to block it out but gets beaten on the inside edge. The keeper fails to grab it in on go. They cross for a bye.
Length ball, on off, tapped to point but not in the gap.
Pitches it full, outside off. Smith drives it to point but is unable to beat the fielder. A tidy over from Jansen comes to an end.
An effort delivery this time by Jansen, wide of off. Steven Smith has no shot to offer.
LEG BYE! A slower one, on a length, going down leg. Travis Head misses his flick. It goes to short fine off his thigh pads. They cross for a leg bye.
Outside off, left alone.
Overpitched, wide of off. Head gets across and drives it to short extra cover.
Jansen goes full and on off. Smith clips it through mid-wicket. They take three runs.
A short ball, on off, it flies off the deck. Travis Head shoulders his arms at it.
Back of a length, on off, shaping away a bit. Travis Head looks to chase it but gets beaten on the outside edge.
On off, blocked out.

Travis Head remains at the crease as the third umpire confirms that the ball bumped before Dean Elgar gathers it. On a length, around off, shaping away a touch. Travis Head gets a thick outside edge. It goes to Dean Elgar inthe slip cordon, although he is unsure ater he pouches it. The umpire takes it upstairs to confirm with the soft-signal of not out. The replays go in favour of the batter.
Slightly short, on off. Head hops inside his crease and blocks it to the off side.
Anrich Nortje gets some extra bounce off the deck. It is a good-length ball, on off. Head hops and defends it back to the bowler.
Much fuller, outside off, shaping away a bit. Smith squeezes it through point for a brace.
A short ball, outside off. Steven Smith shuffles and lets it be.
Jansen bends hia back hard and serves a short ball, in the channel. Steven Smith picks up the delivery early and shoulders his arms at it.
Good length, on fourth stump. Head taps it to covers. Rassie van der Dussen there overthrows and the batters sneak a single.
It is full this time, swinging into the batter. Travis Head gets pinged on his pads as he misses to tuck it away. It is going down leg.
Back of a length, wide of off. Left alone.
Goes full, on off stump. Steven Smith gets on his front foot and blocks it to the left of backward point. Keshav Maharaj dives to that side and makes a half-stop.
It is a length ball, in the channel. Moves away a touch. Steven Smith is drawn into the shot but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Travis Head gets off the mark. It is a length ball, sliding down leg. Head clips it behind square on the leg side for a single.
Full length, on off. Head blocks it to point.

FIVE WIDES! A sharp bouncer, on middle. This one flies over the batter's head. This is even away from the keeper's reach. It races away to the third man fence. The umpire also signals a wide due to height.
Travis Head is the new man in.

OUT! CAUGHT! Anrich Nortje gets his man and Australia are suddenly three wickets down! This is pure pace from Anrich Nortje as he bowls this one back of a length and just outside off at 142 clicks. Usman Khawaja gets squared up as he looks to fend this off his backfoot and the ball takes the outside edge and flies to third slip. Simon Harmer is on the field as a substitute fielder and he is placed in the slip cordon. He takes a fine catch to send the Australian opener back to the pavilion and South Africa are finding a way to stay alive in this game.
Commentary.Howout: c sub Simon Harmer b Anrich Nortje

Commentary.Commentary: FOUR! Anrich Nortje has been welcomed into the attack with a boundary! He bowls this one on a good length but strays onto the pads. Usman Khawaja clips this off his pads and the ball races away to deep square leg for four runs.
Pulls his length back a fraction and bowls this in line with the stumps. Steven Smith defends this back towards the bowler.
Good-length delivery once again moving away from the off stump. Steven Smith is watchful and leaves this one alone as well.
This is well outside off on a good length. Steven Smith gets across to the off side and leaves the ball alone.
This is on a good length and outside off. Steven Smith plays for the in-swinging delivery but the ball keeps its line and goes through to the keeper.
Bowls this on a good length and angles this away from the batter. Steven Smith leaves this one alone.

NO BALL and FOUR RUNS! Marco Jansen goes full this time and outside the off stump. Steven Smith gets a confident stride forward and strokes this towards deep cover. The ball does not reach the ropes but there are able to run four runs. Marco Jansen has overstepped so it will be an extra run as well.
Steven Smith is the new batter to make his way out to the crease.

OUT! CAUGHT! Big, big wicket for South Africa as the man in form Marnus Labuschagne has to make the long walk back to the shed! What an inspired change from Dean Elgar as he brings Marco Jansen into the attack and the tall pacer claims a wicket on the very first delivery.  This is bowled full and well outside the off pole, drawing the in-form Marnus Labuschagne to go for a driven stroke. He oblidges and the ball takes the outside edge to fly into the hands on Dean Elgar at second slip. The skipper looks pumped up and he knows how crucial this wicket is. Australia are two down and this is propably this first time they are in this situation so early in a game since this season began.
Commentary.Howout: c Dean Elgar b Marco Jansen

Commentary.Commentary: Bowls this one outside off and on a good length. Usman Khawaja lets this one go through to the keeper.
Gets this one to come back in sharply on a good length. Usman Khawaja gets beaten on the inside edge and gets hit on the thigh pads.
Strays onto the pads on a shorter length. Marnus Labuschagne tucks this down to fine leg for a single.
Continues bowling back of a length and outside off. Marnus Labuschagne looks to defend but gets a thick outside edge towards point.
Bowls this slightly short as well and outside off. Marnus Labuschagne is well behind the ball as he defends this solidly.
Lungi Ngidi bowls this back of a length and outside off, Usman Khawaja goes on the back foot and punches this towards covet for a single.
Goes fuller this time and outside the off pole, Marnus Labuschagne knocks this back towards the bowler.
Bowls this short and outside off. Marnus Labuschagne gets on his toes to block this but is squared up and the ball hits the bat and falls into the pitch.
On a good length and well outside off. Marnus Labuschagne shoulders his arms to this one.
Continues bowling back of a length and angling into the leg. Usman Khawaja uses the depth of the crease and flicks this to deep backward square leg for a single.
Bowls this one back of a length and in line with the stumps. Usman Khawaja goes back in the crease and tucks this to the leg side.
Kagiso Rabada goes 'round the wicket to the southpaw and bowls this on a good length, outside off. Usman Khawaja happy to leave this one alone.
Bowls this on a good length and outside off. Marnus Labuschagne is solidly behind this one as he defends it towards cover.

Lungi Ngidi bowls a good length delivery coming in sharply into the batter from a good length. Marnus Labuschagne looks to block but gets beaten on the inside edge. The ball hits him high on the back leg and the South African are up in appeal. The bowler does not seem too interested but Dean Elgar opts for the review. Hotspot and Snicko both confirm there is no inside edge but Ball Tracking shows that the ball is doing over the stumps. The onfield decision remains and South Africa lose a review.
Bowls this in line with the stumps on a good length. Marnus Labuschagne tucks this down towards short leg.
Goes outside off this time on a good length. Marnus Labuschagne gets his front foot forward but lets the ball through to the keeper.
Strays onto the pads on a good length. Marnus Labuschagne clips this towards deep backward square leg for a couple of runs,
Lungi Ngidi bowls this on a good length but angles it down leg. Marnus Labuschagne is unable to get bat on this as it goes through to the keeper.
Strays down leg side this time on a fuller length. Usman Khawaja misses his flick and Kyle Verreynne does really well diving to his right to stop the ball.
Goes full this time and outside off. Usman Khawaja knocks this straight to short cover.
Bowls this on a good length and just outside off. Usman Khawaja defends this back down the pitch towards the bowler.

Bowls this one slightly back of a length and outside off. Usman Khawaja looks to get down the wicket but lets it go at the last moment. The ball is really close to the stumps but seems like the batter trusted the bounce in the wicket.
Goes fuller this time and angled into the stumps. Usman Khawaja blocks this back down the pitch towards the bowler.

FOUR! That is the first boundary for Usman Khawaja! Kagiso Rabada goes 'round the wicket and bangs this in short, outside off. Usman Khawaja gets hold of this as he pulls this towards deep square leg for four runs.
Bowls this one back of a length and in line with the stumps. Usman Khawaja gets back in the crease and tucks the ball to the right of mid-wicket for a single to get off the mark.
Goes full and angles this into the stumps. Usman Khawaja blocks this towards mid on.
Bowls this wider outside off on a good length and Usman Khawaja does not bother with this one at all.
Bowls this one really close to the off pole and on a good length. Usman Khawaja judges the angle well and lets this one through to the keeper.
Gets this one to nip back in and on a good length. Usman Khawaja continues to raise his arms and let it through.
Lungi Ngidi bowls this from 'round the wicket and serves this on a good length outside off. Usman Khawaja raises  his arms and leaves this one alone.
Bangs this in short and outside the off pole. Marnus Labuschagne sways out of the way and lets it through to the keeper. Maiden over from Kagiso Rabada.
Goes slightly fuller this time and outside the off stump. Marnus Labuschagne offers no shot once again.
Wider outside off on a good length. Marnus Labuschagne happy to leave this one alone as well.
On a good length once again and outside off, Marnus Labuschagne decides to leave this one alone.
Bowls this one on a good length and outside off. Marnus Labuschagne looks to defend but gets squared up. Takes the outside edge of the bat and falls short of the slip fielder.
A short ball, wide of off, swinging in late. Marnus Labuschagne shoulders his arms at it.
Touch fuller, on off. Usman Khawaja eases it back to the bowler. A maiden to start with for Lungi Ngidi.
Goes full. attacking the stumps. Usman Khawaja shuffles and blocks it to the left of the bowler.
Fraction short, wide of off. Usman Khawaja watches it sail past him.
A length ball, coming in with the angle, on off pole/ Usman Khawaja stays back and defends it to point.
Ngidi comes 'round the wicket and dishes a length ball, wide of off. Usman Khawaja has no shot to offer.
Ngidi serves it outside off. Usman Khawaja is happy to let it go.
Lungi Ngidi will share the attack and bowl from the other end.

FOUR! Nicely played. A length ball, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne steers it through the gap between backward point and gully. It races away to the boundary. An entertaining first over from Rabada comes to an end.
Back of a length, wide of off, nips in late. Marnus Labuschagne shoulders his arms at it.
On a length, on top of off. Marnus Labuschagne gets it out to safety.
FOUR! Easy pickings for Marnus Labuschagne. It is a length ball, sliding down leg. Marnus Labuschagne stays back and flicks it down to fine leg for four runs.
A length ball, on off, blocked out.
Marnus Labuschagne makes his way out at number 3.

OUT! CAUGHT! David Warner departs on a golden duck. South Africa have taken a wicket of the very first delivery. Kagiso Rabada steams in serves a short ball, on off. The ball gets big on Warner, as ot extracts some extra bounce off the deck. David Warner hops and tries to block it out. The ball takes the inside edge and oes over short leg. Khaya Zondo there reacts sharply, leaps and takes a one-handed stunner.
Commentary.Howout: c Khaya Zondo b Kagiso Rabada

Commentary.Commentary: We are back for the final inning of the Test match and Australia have a really small target to chase down. The umpires are out in the middle and the South African players are in a huddle hoping to pull off a miracle. David Warner and Usman Khawaja are the openers for Australia and they will want to get their team home without any hiccups. Kagiso Rabada has the new ball in his hand and will begin proceedings. Let's play...
... FOURTH INNINGS ...

A dominating performance by the Australian bowlers here. In the final session, South Africa lost two wickets on consecutive deliveries in the second over after the break. Everyone expected South Africa to post a target in single digits but Khaya Zondo played a crucial knock of 36 runs off 85 balls to set the target of 34 runs. There is nothing to talk much about the batting performance of South Africa as they got bundled out for just 99 runs. For Australia, it was Pat Cummins who stood out with the ball with his five-wicket haul. The skipper has led his team from the front here and the Aussies already have one foot over the victory line. Right then, the hosts need 34 runs to take a lead in this Test series. Do join us shortly for the final innings of this Test match.

OUT! CAUGHT! Pat Cummins picks up his five-fer. He bowls this slightly short and into the batter, allowing the pitch to do the rest. The ball rises sharply off the strip and forces Lungi Ngidi to sway out of the way but he fails to get his bat down in time. The ball takes the outside edge and goes into the hands of David Warner at slip. He makes not mistake taking this one and hands the ball to the umpire before racing off to prepare for his batting. This has been a dominating performance by the hosts as they have bundled South Africa for 99 runs and will have to chase down a target of 34.
Commentary.Howout: c David Warner b Pat Cummins

Commentary.Commentary: A sharp bouncer on middle. Lungi Ngidi sways away from the line of the delivery.
FOUR! Incredible shot. It is very full, wide of off. Lungi Ngidi stands tall and drives it through the line. The ball goes aerially through covers and into the boundary for four runs.
Back of a length, on top of off. Ngidi gets his blade high and blocks it out.
Bangs this in short and angling down leg. Khaya Zondo ducks under this one and lets it go through to the keeper. Lungi Ngidi will have strike once again in the next over.
Mitchell Starc bowls this one really wide outside off on a fuller length. Khaya Zondo reaches for it but does not connect.
Goes full this time and angles this into the stumps from outside off. Khaya Zondo goes deep in the crease and blocks this away solidly.
Bowls this one on a good length and angling down leg. Khaya Zondo looks to clip this fine but misses as it goes through to the keeper.
This is bowled a touch fuller and outside off, Lungi Ngidi knocks this towards deep cover-point and they settle for a single.
Bowls this on a good length and outside off. Lungi Ngidi knocks this towards the mid off fielder.
Pat Cummins fires this one way down leg side and this enables him to keep Khaya Zondo on strike. Lungi Ngidi will face the start of the next over.

This is on a good length and angled into the stumps. Khaya Zondo swings across the line and gets beaten. The ball misses the off pole by a fraction and the players around the bat feel there is a nick. With three reviews left Pat Cummins decides to go upstairs. Hotspot and Snicko confirm no bat involved.

FOUR! This has been dismissed away and Khaya Zondo is giving the South African fans something to cheer about! Pat Cummins goes full this time and outside the off pole. Khaya Zondo clears his front foot out of the way and thumps this towards long off for the third boundary in the over.
FOUR! That has been swatted away! Pat Cummins bowls this slightly short and outside off. Khaya Zondo pulls this towards deep mid-wicket and collects another four runs.

FOUR! A stroke of good fortune! Pat Cummins bowls this on a good length and just outside the off pole. Khaya Zondo puts his bat towards the ball with absolutely no foot movement. Gets an inside edge that flies away to fine leg for four runs.
Pat Cummins starts the over with a short ball outside off. Khaya Zondo gets on top of the bounce and pulls this towards deep square leg. No run taken.
On a fuller length once again and outside the off stump. Lungi Ngidi hits this firmly towards the mid off fielder. South Africa lead by 16 runs.
Goes full and just outside the off pole. Lungi Ngidi looks to drive this on the up but gets beaten.
Fires in a yorker this time, in line with the stumps. Khaya Zondo flicks this towards deep square leg and takes a single this time.
Bowls this one back of a length and outside off. Khaya Zondo mishits his pull shot but it lands safely to the right of mid-wicket. They do not take a run.
Goes fuller this time outside the off pole. Khaya Zondo leans into the drive and knocks this deep cover-point for a couple of runs. Good running from the pair.
Mitchell Starc bowls this on a good length and just outside off. Khaya Zondo feels for the ball and gets beaten all ends up.
On a good length and angled into the stumps. Lungi Ngidi blocks this towards mid-wicket and survives.
Goes full and angles this into the pads. Khaya Zondo clips this towards deep square leg and takes a single this time. Lungi Ngidi has one ball to face.
This is on a good length and in line with the stumps. Khaya Zondo defends this solidly back towards the bowler.
BEATEN! It is a length ball, in the channel. Zondo tries to chase it but misses. The ball zips past the outside edge.

FOUR! That has been put away cleverly! Pat Cummins bowls this short and offers width outside off. Khaya Zondo cuts thsi over the slips cordon and collects four runs as the ball races away to the deep backward point boundary.
Pat Cummins bowls this on a good length and angled into the pads. Khaya Zondo pulls this towards deep backward square leg but does not take the run.
Angled down leg on a good length. Lungi Ngidi looks to clip this fine but misses. Goes towards third man off his pads but Khaya Zondo refuses the leg bye this time.
Unplayable! Mitchell Starc bowls this on a good length and angled into the stumps. Lungi Ngidi backs away and looks to block. Gets beaten by the pace.
FOUR! Nicely played! It is full, outside off. Lungi Ngidi opens the face and steers it past backward point for a boundary. The lead moves to 8 runs.
Very full and straight, on off. Lungi Ngidi blocks it back to the bowler.

A dot now! Starc angles in a length ball, outside off, that leaves the batter with some away movement. It also extracts some extra bounce off the deck. Lungi Ngidi gets beaten on the outside edge as he goes back and tries to block it out.

Mitchell Starc bowls this on a good length and outside off. Khaya Zondo taps this into the off side and looks for a single. He gets the number 11 on strike and this does not seem like a good move with five balls left in the over.
Lungi Ngidi is the last man in.

OUT! CAUGHT! Another one bites the dust and the Australian skipper Pat Cummins is on a Hat-trick! He bowls this on a good length and angles this into the stumps. Anrich Nortje put his bat in front of the ball to keep it away from his pads and the stumps. The ball takes the outside edge and flies into the bucket-sized palms of Cameron Green at gully. South Africa are one wicket away from surrendering this game and Australia have their opponents by the throat now.
Commentary.Howout: c Cameron Green b Pat Cummins

Commentary.Commentary: Anrich Nortje comes in at the crease now.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! That short ball seems to have shaken Kagiso Rabada up! Pat Cummins goes back to bowling on a fraction fuller length just outside the off pole. Kagiso Rabada is on the back foot and pushes at the ball. Takes the outside edge of his bat and flies to the keeper's left. Alex Carey takes a fine catch moving in that direction and South Africa have now lost their eighth wicket. The lead is still 3 runs and South Africa dig themselves deeper into a hole.
Commentary.Howout: c Alex Carey b Pat Cummins

Commentary.Commentary: Pulls his length back and bowls this short, in line with the stumps. Kagiso Rabada sways out of the way in the nick of time.
Even more fuller this time and going away from the bat. Kagiso Rabada goes hard at the ball and is beaten once again.
Goes a tad bit fuller and angles this away from the left-hander. Kagiso Rabada looks to drive through the line but gets beaten
Pat Cummins bowls this on a good length and in line with the stumps. Kagiso Rabada blocks this towards the mid off fielder.
Pat Cummins to steam in from the other end.
Bowls this on a good length and into the pads. Kagiso Rabada clips this to deep square leg and takes a single. South Africa lead by three runs.
Continues bowling on a good length and outside off. Khaya Zondo taps this towards cover-point and takes a quick single.
This is on a good length and just outside the off stump. Khaya Zondo looks to block and gets an outside edge towards the gully fielder.
Bowls this on a yorker length and in line with the stumps. Kagiso Rabada digs this out straight past the bowler and they take a single. South Africa have taken the lead.

An absolute beauty! Bowls this on a good length and just outside off. The ball is angled into the stumps and Kagiso Rabada looks to block. The ball straightens after pitching and beats the outside edge.
Starc sarts with a length ball, on off. Kagiso Rabada blocks it out to safety.

The final session is set to begin. The Australian players take the field. Followed by Kagiso Rabada and Khaya Zondo who walk out to bat for South Africa. The scores are level at the moment and now the South African tail-enders have their task cut out here.
... Day 2, Session 3 ...

A session that truly belonged to the Aussies. South Africa have managed to cut down the deficit of 66 runs right at the brink of Tea but while losing seven wickets in total. They are way behind in this game and need something special from their tail-enders if they are to delay the victory for the hosts. South Africa came into this session on 3/2. They went on to lose 5 more wickets in the afternoon session. It was Nathan Lyon who came into the attack and broke the gritty stand between Bavuma and Zondo by getting the better of the former. Later, Scott Boland came in and chipped in with a couple of wickets in a single over to make it worse for the opposition. South Africa are placed in a precarious position here. They will be hoping to come back for the final session and bat as long as they can to add some valuable runs on the board for the hosts to chase down. Do join us at 10.50 am IST (5.20 am GMT) to find out how things pan out.
Fires this one full and into the pads. Kagiso Rabada flicks this into the mid-wicket region and takes a single. He will retain strike after the break as the umpires have called for TEA of Day 2.
Kagiso Rabada comes down the track and blocks this full delivery to mid on.
Floated and full, on leg. Kagiso Rabada defends it back to the bowler.
Gets this to spin sharply into the pads on a shorter length. Khaya Zondo tucks this towards deep backward square leg for a single.
Another flighted delivery bowled full and turning in from outside off. Khaya Zondo looks to push at this but gets an inside edge that falls short of the short leg fielder.
Loopy delivery bowled full and outside off. Khaya Zondo gets a good stride forward and defends this to the cover fielder.
Bowls this on a good length and outside the off pole. Kagiso Rabada is happy to get a look in and leaves this one alone.
Kagiso Rabada is the new man in.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Mitchell Starc gets his man and this time induces the outside edge! Bowls this on a good length and just outside off. Keshav Maharaj leans into the shot but the ball swings away from the bat. Takes a faint edge as it goes through to Alex Carey behind the wicket who takes a comfortable catch. Keshav Maharaj's short inning has come to an end and South Africa find themselves seven down now. Australia have commanded proceedings and look destined to seal this game.
Commentary.Howout: c Alex Carey b Mitchell Starc

Commentary.Commentary: FOUR! That is a lucky boundary! Mitchell Starc bowls this on a good length and this time gets the ball to keep its line coming in from outside off. Keshav Maharaj pushes at the ball and gets an inside edge that flies towards fine leg for four more runs. 2 runs away from making Australia bat once again.
FOUR! That has been put away nicely! A low full toss this time outside the off pole. Keshav Maharaj gets forward and strokes this towards deep point for four runs.
Bowls this one on a good length and just outside off. Keshav Maharaj plays for the line of the ball once again and gets beaten by the movement away from the bat.
Mitchell Starc starts off with a beauty! Bowls this one is really full and just outside off from 'round the wicket. Gets the ball to straighten after pitching and beats the outside edge of the bat.
Continues bowling short and gets the ball to turn into the pads. Khaya Zondo plays this with soft hands towards short leg.
Bowls short once again and just outside off. Keshav Maharaj goes deep in the crease once again and cuts this to the fielder at deep backward point for a single.
This is a fraction short and spinning into the pads, Keshav Maharaj taps this towards short leg.

FOUR! Great use of the crease and this should release some pressure! Nathan Lyon bowls this short and gets it to turn into the stumps. Keshav Maharaj rocks back and makes room to cut this towards deep backward point for a boundary.
Loopy delivery bowled full and outside off. Keshav Maharaj lunges forward and defends this solidly towards cover.
Nathan Lyon flights this full and outside off, and gets the ball to spin into the stumps. Keshav Maharaj blocks this towards mid off.
Full once again and angled into the pads. Khaya Zondo clips this towards the short mid on fielder. A maiden over from Scott Boland as the pressure builds on South Africa.
Continues to bowl full and just outside the off pole. Khaya Zondo defends this solidly towards point.
Goes fuller this time and angles this in from outside off. Khaya Zondo gets his front foot forward to block and gets an inside edge onto his pads. The ball rolls towards cover.
Bowls this one slightly short and outside off. Khaya Zondo looks to cut but gets a bottom edge towards the gully fielder.
This is on a good length as well and just outside off. Khaya Zondo gets across the line of the ball and defends this into the pitch.
Scott Boland bowls this on a good length and into the pads. Khaya Zondo misses his blocks and gets hit on the pads.
Good turn on this one as well as it spins into the legs on a shorter length. Keshav Maharaj plays this with soft hands towards short leg.
On a fuller length this time and outside off. Keshav Maharaj dabs this down to the off side.
Gets this one to spin down leg side on a shorter length. Keshav Maharaj is watchful as he lets it go through to the keeper.
Bowls this one a fraction short and spinning into the pads. Keshav Maharaj manages to tap this down to the leg side.
Flights this one full and outside off. Keshav Maharaj gets a good stride forward and blocks this into the pitch.
That has been driven beautifully! Nathan Lyon floats this one full and outside off. Keshav Maharaj strokes this to the left of mid off and takes a couple of runs.
Goes full again, just outside off. Keshav Maharaj pushes it to point and scampers across for a quick single.
Ths is full, on middle and leg. Keshav Maharaj plays it to the right of the bowler.
Keshav Maharaj strides out to the middle now.

OUT! TIMBER! An absolute jaffa. It is certainly very difficult to keep Boland at bay once he has tasted blood. He gets his second wicket of the over and South Africa slip further. A dream wicket for any seamer, this. It is a length ball that lands outside off and nips in a touch off the deck. Marco Jansen stays inside the line and tries to defend it but gets no where near the ball. The ball zips past the outside edge and crashes into the off stump. The crowd at the Gabba is loving every moment.
Commentary.Howout: b Scott Boland

Commentary.Commentary: It is full, angled into the batter. Jansen stays back and nudges it to mid on.
Marco Jansen is the next batter to make his way to the crease.

OUT! CAUGHT AT SLIPS! Scott Boland gets himself into the wicket's column now as he gets rid of Kyle Verreynne on a duck. Boland dishes a length ball, around off. It shapes away a touch. Kyle Verreynne tries to defend it out but gets a thick outside edge. The ball flies to Steven Smith at second slip who makes no mistake. Australia are right on top in this game now.
Commentary.Howout: c Steven Smith b Scott Boland

Commentary.Commentary: It is touch fuller, on off. Zondo blocks it to cover-point off the front foot and crosses.
On off, blocked back to the bowler. A wicket-taking over by Lyon comes to an end.
Kyle Verreynne, South Africa's best batter in the first inning, walk out to the middle.

OUT! LBW! Nathan Lyon finally gets his first wicket. The original decision is out but Bavuma thinks of trying his luck by taking the review. Coming to the delivery, it is tossed up, outside off. It grips and turns in a long way. Bavuma misses his flick and gets pinged on his pads. The appeal is made and the finger goes up in a flash. The Snicko confirms no bat is involved. The Ball Tracking shows it is umpire's call on the ball hitting the wickets. South Africa do not lose a review here but do lose their man.
Commentary.Howout: lbw b Nathan Lyon

Commentary.Commentary: FOUR! Nicely played. It is full and on middle. Temba Bavuma reverse hits it past backward point and gets a boundary.
On off, Bavuma goes back and pushes it to cover.
It is looped up, full and outside off. It turns in a long way. Bavuma gets pinged on hispads but outside the line.
Tosses it up, full and outside off. Bavuma pushes it to covers.
Boland serves a length ball, on fourth stump. Zondo looks to drive it away but gets an inside edge on his pads.
A length ball, wide of off.Zondo does not go after it.
On off, blocked out.
A sharp bouncer, on off. Zondo looks to latch onto it but misses.
An in-tucker, on a length from outside off. Bavuma pushes it through cover for a single.
A good-length ball, in the corridor of uncertainty. It gets some extra bounce off the deck. Bavuma lets it be.
Just a single off the over. It is full and on off. Zondo blocks it out.
This is full, sliding down leg. Zondo clips it to short fine leg.
Zondo presses forward to this full delivery and blocks it into the deck.
It turns in a long way from outside off. Zondo gets pinged high on his thigh pads.
Flatter and short, wide of off. Zondo shuffles and leaves.
Full, on off, pushed to cover for one.
Goes a tab bit fuller and into the stumps. Temba Bavuma clips this to the right of mid-wicket and takes a quick run to retain strike.
Beaten this time! Scott Boland continues to bowl on a good length and outside off. Temba Bavuma pushes at the ball this time and it misses his outside edge by a fraction.
Bowls this on a good length and just outside off. Temba Bavuma plays inside the line of the ball as he leaves it alone for the keeper to collect.
Goes fuller this time and just outside off. Temba Bavuma looks to block but gets an inside edge towards deep square leg and they run well to complete two runs.
This is on a good length and just outside the off pole. Temba Bavuma hangs his bat out to dry and gets beaten all ends up.
Scott Boland bowls this one really full and just outside off. Temba Bavuma digs this one out towards mid off.

Both batters are ready to sweep the ball. Nathan Lyon goes full once again and outside off. Temba Bavuma gets his front foot across the stumps and sweeps this to the deep backward square leg fielder for another run.
Goes full once again and outside the off stump. Khaya Zondo connects his sweep and gets the ball to deep backward square leg for a single.
Bowls this one short and spinning into the pads. Temba Bavuma goes deep in the crease and tucks this uppishly towards square leg for a single.
Loops this full and outside off. Temba Bavuma gets his front foot forward and defends this towards cover.
Flights this one as well and bowls this outside off. Temba Bavuma attempts the sweep shot but misses.
Nathan Lyon floats the first ball full and outside off. Temba Bavuma taps this towards short third man.
It will be spin for the first time as Nathan Lyon has been brought into the attack.
On a good length this time and outside off. Khaya Zondo taps this towards backward point.
Bowls this full and angled into the pads. The ball goes on to hit the pad and there is a huge appeal. The umpire says not out and replays confirm there is a clear inside edge.

Bangs this in short and in line with the stumps, this is probably cause Scott Boland saw the batter take a couple of steps forward. Khaya Zondo walks down the pitch but ducks and lets the ball goes through to the keeper.
Bowls this on a good length as well and just outside off. Khaya Zondo blocks this solidly towards cover.
This is bowled on a good length and outside off. Temba Bavuma dabs this towards backward point and takes a quick single.
Scott Boland starts off after the break with a full delivery outside off. Temba Bavuma gets a confident stride forward and strokes this through covers for a couple of runs.

DRINKS! South Africa lost a wicket early in the first hour of the second session with Pat Cummins bowling with some serious pace and fire. Temba Bavuma and Khaya Zondo have begun building a partnership and it is vital for the visitors they continue.
This is outside off once again and Zondo has no shot to offer.
Slightly shorter, wide of off. It shapes in late. Zondo leaves it alone for the keeper.
Outside off, left alone.
NO BALL AND FOUR! A short ball, on the bodyline. Zondo swivels and pulls it to deep square leg for a boundary. The umpire signals a no ball as the bowler oversteps.
Cummins bends his back hard now and goes for the bouncer, on off. Zondo ducks under it.
Temba Bavuma taps this length ball to covers for a single this time.
Full, on fourth stump, defended to point.
Good length, outside off. Zondo gets beaten in the process as he tries to block it out.
Boland serves it full, on off. Bavuma gets it to mid on off the inner half. The batters take a quick single.
On off, defended solidly on the front foot.
Boland angles in a length ball. It lands and shapes away a bit. Bavuma stays back and tries to defend it out but misses.
Woah! It is a length ball, outside off, shapes in a bit. Bavuma tries to block it away but misses.
Goes full, on off. Bauma drives it back to the bowler.
Fuller, around off. Zondo defends it to point.
It is a length ball, in the channel of uncertainty. Zondo gets beaten on the outside edge as he tries to block it away.
FOUR! Extremely well played. It is a length ball, on fourth stump. Khaya Zondo stands tall and punches it through the line on the up. The ball races through covers for a boundary.
It is very full, in-line with the stumps. Zondo blocks it to the off side.
Outside off, left alone.
Cummins serves it on a length, on off, it shapes away a bit. Zondo tries to defend it out but gets beaten. The ball zips past the outside edge.
A length ball now. It lands outside off and nips in off the deck. Temba Bavuma tries to block it but misses and gets pinged high on his pads.
FOUR! Temba Bavuma is finding his feet here. It is a half-volley, outside off. Bavuma drives it through covers for a boundary. One of the sweetest cover drives of this inning.
Four dots on the trot! Length and on off. Bavuma opens the face and works it to point.
Too full and straight, around middle. Bavuma eases back to the bowler with full face of the blade.
It is outside off, on a length. Bavuma leaves it alone for the keeper.
This full delivery is driven to covers.
It is a bouncer, on off. Zondo ducks under it. Only a single off the over then. It has been very difficult for the visitors to score at a brisk rate.
Cummins serves it on a good-length, on fifth stump. Zondo tries to block it but does so inside the line.
A length ball, around off, shaping away a touch. Khaya Zondo gets it to point off the outer half.
It is full and on off. Zondo gets forward and pats it back to the bowler.
What a stop! It is a short ball, wide of off. Zondo stays back and cuts it hard to the right of point. Nathan Lyon there moves to that side and makes a sharp stop.
A short ball, on off. Bavuma taps it to cover and scampers across for a quick single.
Boland serves it full and on fourth stump. Zondo gets and outside edge to gully. It meets the fielder in slips at a bounce as he plays it with soft hands. Boland gets a maiden off his first.
Five dots in a row now as Zondo blocks this full delivery back to the bowler.
Full, attacking the stumps. Zondo presses forward and defends it to cover-point.
Good length, on off. Zondo pushes it to mid off.
CLOSE! A well judged leave. Back of a length, wide of off. It nips back in late. Zondo shuffles and shoulders his arms as well.
Boland starts his spell with a jaffa. It is a short ball, in the channel. Khaya Zondo looks to block it away but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Scott Boland has been brought into the attack.
In the channel this time. It flies off the deck as well. Temba Bavuma does not chase it.
Pat Cummins serves it full, on fifth stump. Temba Bavuma tries to push it away but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Back of a length, coming in from outside off. Bavuma goes back and blocks it to the leg side.
An inswinger this time, full and on off. Temba Bavuma gets a thick outside edge as he tries to block it. Although, it lands short of Usman Khawaja in the slip cordon.
FOUR! Timed to perfection. It is overpitched, wide outside off. Temba Bavuma leans into it and carves it through covers for a fine boundary.
Much fuller, around off. It nips back into the batter. Bavuma looks to drive it away but gets an inside edge on his pads.
Zondo stays inside the crease and blocks it to covers with soft hands.
Shorter now, outside off. Zondo lets it be. Three dots on the trot now.
It is full, angled across. Zondo opens the face and pushes it to covers.
Starc serves it on a length, outside off. Zondo has no shot to offer.
Short and on off. Bavuma pushes it to cover-point for a single.

OUCH! That must've hurt. It is a short ball, in the channel. It flies off the deck. Temba Bavuma hangs back and shoulders his arms at it. Although, he does no read it well as the ball hits him hard on his elbow.
It is angled in full, into the pads. Zondo hangs back and flicks it to mid-wicket. Just two runs off the over.
Pat Cummins dishes it full and wide outside off. Zondo drives it past extra cover. They take a couple before the fielder cuts it out.
Length, on off stump. Zondo shuffles and nudges it to the leg side.
This a good-length ball, on leg stump. Zondo flicks it to square leg off his hips.
Fuller, on off. Zondo presses forward and pushes it back to the bowler.
Short, outside off. Zondo lets it be.
Full again, on off. Bavuma blocks it out.
Very full, around off. Bavuma knocks it into covers with soft hands.
Full, attacking the stumps. Zondo defends it to cover and crosses.
Nicely played. It is fuller in length, wide of off. Bavuma leans in and creams it through covers. Marnus Labuschagne gives it a chase and saves a run here as the batters take three.
This is a length ball, on off, it jags back in. Temba Bavuma gets an inside edge on his pads.
Starc goes full, down leg. Bavuma tries to glance it around the corner but misses.
Gets this one closer to the stumps on a good length. Khaya Zondo gets squared up but manages to block this into the off side.

This is on a good length as well and wide outside off. Khaya Zondo pushes at this and gets a thick outside edge to the right of gully. Cameron Green puts in a dive and stops the ball to restrict the single.
Bowls this on a good length and outside the off pole. Khaya Zondo gets across the stumps and leaves the ball alone.

It could've been two wickets in two. It is a length ball, around off, moving away a bit. Zondo gets a thick outside edge as he looks to defend it out. It goes low to the left of Green on gully. He dives to that side and gathers the ball with both hands. Usman Khawaja had already started celebrating but Green cuts it short as he says that it took a bump.
Khaya Zondo comes into bat with his team in a whole lot of trouble.

OUT! CAUGHT! Cameron Green times his jump to perfection and takes a stunning catch at gully. Sarel Erwee holes out this time. South Africa lose their third wicket now. This is getting worse and worse for the visitors. Cummins serves it short, in the channel. Sarel Erwee opts to leave it alone but his bat it still hanging above his head. The ball takes the edge and flies high over Green at gully. He leaps and gathers it with both hands. The Aussies are truly delighted here.
Commentary.Howout: c Cameron Green b Pat Cummins

Commentary.Commentary: Sarel Erwee stays back to this short ball, on middle and leg. He swivels on the back foot and pulls it to deep square leg for two runs.
This is angled across on a shorter length. Bavuma shuffles and shoulders his arms at it. Two maidens on the trot for the Aussies here.
Outside off, left alone.
Fuller, on off. Bavuma eases it back to the bowler.
Mitchell Starc serves it on a length, angling across the right-hander. Temba Bavuma looks to block it away but does so inside the line.
EIght dot on the trot now! It is a length ball, wide outside off, shaping away. Bavuma does not go chasing it.
This is angled across on a shorter length, wide of off. It jags back in off the deck. Bavuma leaves it for the keeper.
Who will bowl from the other end?
Pat Cummins starts the afternoon session with a maiden. A length ball, on off, nips away a bit. Erwee looks to play at it but misses.
This one lands outside off and straightens a bit. Sarel Erwee hangs back and tries to flick it away but takes a blow on his pads. Pat Cummins and company appeal but the umpire keeps his finger low.
A sharp bouncer now. Sarel Erwee ducks under it.
BEATEN! This is much fuller, wide of off. Sarel Erwee looks to go for the booming drive but gets beaten in the process.
Pat Cummins is asking the right questions straightaway. It is a length ball, on fourth stump. Sarel Erwee tries to chase it but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Nicely bowled! It is on a good length, close to the body around off. It flies off the deck as well. Erwee shuffles and shoulders his arms at it.

We are back for the second session on Day 2 and the game has moved forward pretty quickly The umpires make their way out to the middle and the Australian players are in a huddle beyond the boundary line. They spread out and take their positions in the field and the South African batters, Temba Bavuma and Sarel Erwee stride out to the pitch. Pat Cummins will carry on with his spell after the break. Let's go...
... DAY 2, SESSION 2 ...

This game could get over in a hurry unless Temba Bavuma and Sarel Erwee build a partnership after the break. South Africa will be hoping their batters show more fight in this inning and if they are able to get a lead near the 200-run mark it will be a tough target for the hosts to chase down. The Aussies will be eager to wrap up the South African inning at the earliest and begin the series with a dominating win. Will they be able to wreck through the Proteas' batting line-up? Or will we see a fightback from the visitors? Join us as at 8.30 am IST (3 am GMT) as we try to get our answers in the second session of Day 2.

South Africa did not get off to the best of starts with the ball this morning as the leaked runs at a steady pace. The pair of Travis Head and Cameron Green put on a 36-run partnership in just 37 balls but the introduction of Marco Jansen turned the momentum back in the visitor's favor. The two set batters were dismissed in the same over but Alex Carey and Mitchell Starc played handy cameos to push the lead beyond 50. Lungi Ngidi claimed one wicket and Kagiso Rabada claimed two more to wrap up the Australian inning. They did go into the inning break with some renewed rigor but the two early wickets have got them chasing the game once again.

Advantage Australia! The hosts find themselves in the driver’s seat at the end of the first session of Day 2. They have a lead of 63 runs on the board and have already claimed two wickets in their second outing. South Africa have got off to the worst possible start losing their skipper Dean Elgar and Rassie van der Dussen early as the Australian opening bowlers have been on the money from the word go. Pat Cummins led by example dismissing his counterpart in his first over and Mitchell Starc made Rassie van der Dussen his 300th Test wicket. South Africa have their work cut out if they are to get anything out of this game.
Full and on off. Bavuma pushes this to mid off. For no run though. That will be LUNCH ON DAY 2.
This is full and on off, shapes in a bit late. Temba Bavuma tries to block it but misses. He gets pinged on his pads. Starc makes an appeal but the umpire shows no interest.
A bit shorter, angling across the right-hander. Bavuma leaves it alone for the keeper.
Much fuller, on middle and leg. Bavuma presses forward and blocks it out to safety.
Once again it is wide of off and Bavuma is happy to keep his blade to himself.
Outside off, left alone by Bavuma.
This is full, angling across, outside off. Sarel Erwee leaves it for the keeper.
Good length, on fourth stump. Erwee hangs back and defends it to the off side.
Sarel Erwee leaves this length ball which is outside off.
Cummins goes full, attacking the stumps. Erwee defends it back to the bowler.
On off. Erwee blocks it out solidly.
Full and on off, blocked back.
Fuller, on off. Bavuma presses forward and defends it to covers.
Temba Bavuma makes his way out to the middle.

OUT! TIMBER! Mitchell Starc does what he does best. He just keeps on taking wickets with the new ball and this time he records his 300th Test wicket for the Aussies. An incredible achievement for the left-arm pacer. Starc serves it full, angled across the right hander. Rassie van der Dussen is drawn into the shot as he hangs his blade away from his body to defend it. The ball though jags back into the batter off the deck. It beats Rassie van der Dussen on the inside edge. The ball sneaks through the gap between bat and pad to shatter the stumps. South Africa are in a spot of bother here.
Commentary.Howout: b Mitchell Starc

Commentary.Commentary: Very full, angling across the right-hander. Rassie van der Dussen watches it sail past him.
Sarel Erwee pats this length ball to covers and crosses.
This is a bit fuller, angled into the batter but shapes away a touch to ping Erwee on his pads. Mitchell Starc makes a stifled appeal. No interest shown by the umpire.
Starc starts with a length ball, wide of off. Erwee lets it be.
Outside off, left alone.

Too high! Cummins serves a length ball. It lands on outside off and jags back in a long way. Rassie van der Dussen shoulders his arms as he does not anticipate any movement here and takes a huge blow high on his thigh pads.
Rassie van der Dussen come out to bat at number 3.

OUT! LBW! The skipper draws first blood here. It looks to be plumb and the umpire raises his finger in a flash. Dean Elgar has a long chat with his partner and takes the review for lbw. Coming to the delivery, it is a length ball, angled across. It pitches around off and straightens a touch. Dean Elgar hangs back and looks to flick it away but gets pinged on his pads. The appeal is made and the umpire agrees. The Snicko later confirms that no bat is involved, while the Ball Tracking confirms that it is umpire's call on ball hitting the wickets. The on-field decision stands and the Proteas do not lose a review here.
Commentary.Howout: lbw b Pat Cummins

Commentary.Commentary: Much fuller, on off. Dean Elgar leans forward and drives it past the bowler down to long off. The batters take a couple.
Back of a length, shaping across once again. Dean Elgar has no shot to offer.
A short ball, in the channel, angled across. Elgar keeps his eyes on the ball and leaves it watchfully.
Pat Cummins has decided to share the new ball and will bowl from the other end.
Quite full, attacking the stumps. Erwee pushes it to mid on. A great start by Starc.
Still no runs for Erwee or the Proteas. It is a length ball, around off. Erwee looks to block it but misses.
Good length, wide of off. Erwee shoulders his arms at it.
This is simply unplayable. It is much fuller, on off, it lands and nips away off the deck. Sarel Erwee gets beaten on the outside edge as he shuffles and tries to block it off.
Two dots on the trot! It is a short ball, wide of off. Erwee lets it be.
Some movement straightaway. Starc goes full, with some away shape on it, outside off. Erwee leans and drives it into covers.

Right then, that is it from this short Test match. Australia have dominated the first Test and will be eager to win the next game and seal this series. They have accumulated crucial Test Championship points while South Africa will find their second spot on the standings threatened. We move now to the Boxing Day Test which starts on the 26th of December at 5.00 am IST (11.30 pm GMT, the previous day) at the Melbourne Cricket Ground. As you know, our build-up will begin much earlier so do join us for the same. Till then, goodbye and cheers!

Pat Cummins the victorious captain of Australia says that it has been a great couple of days. Informs that it was a tricky wicket but praises Steven Smith and Travis Head for the way they batted. Mentions that he is very happy with his bowlers as they were pretty relentless on this wicket. Adds that Mitchell Starc just keeps on impressing as he is the kind of player that keeps going to sharpen his skills day in and day out. Reckons that all the attention will soon shift to the Boxing Day Test. Ends by saying he cannot wait for the next challenge.

Dean Elgar the skipper of South Africa says that with another 60 runs they would still be in this game. Mentions that he wants to wrap his head around the result. Claims that it is a spicy pitch and it is challenging for the batters. Explains that they can not be prepared any better but the conditions were not good for the batters so he feels they can't really do too much different. Reckons that with a few days' break, they will go back to the drawing board and have some discussions. Ends by saying that if there are two quality bowling attacks then people want to watch them but over 5 days of Test cricket.

Travis Head wins the Player of the Match award for scoring 92 runs in 96 balls in the first inning. He says that the chat was such that they will try to get them off their lengths and not lose wickets to put pressure on the opposition. Mentions, he and Steven Smith aimed to remain positive and get rid of the bad balls. Praises the bowlers for their excellent effort with the ball. He ends by saying he will focus on his recovery now since the next match will be after a few days' break.
Time for the presentations...

Mitchell Starc is up for a chat and he says that it has been a very interesting Test match. Mentions that he is delighted to bring up the milestone and he will surely enjoy the moment. Adds that the last two years have been more consistent and thinks it has been the best phase for his career. On the bowling attack, he says that Josh Hazlewood is, unfortunately, coming from an injury but all they hope for is to support each other whenever they come out in the middle. Nathan Lyon joins in the chat as well. He says that it is pretty amazing to see Mitchell Starc achieve so many things in his career. Informs that Travis Head truly deserves to be the man of the match as he has been consistent with the blade in this Test match in tricky conditions.

The second innings didn't start well for the visitors as they were trailing by 66 runs and apart from Temba Bavuma and Khaya Zondo none of the batters could get going. They were bowled out for 99 runs and Pat Cummins was the main destroyer claiming a five-wicket haul. Mitchell Starc and Scott Boland claimed two wickets each with the former reaching 300 wickets in Test cricket. With a target of 34 to achieve, it looked like a routine run chase but Kagiso Rabada made things interesting by taking another four-wicket haul. Had they scored 50 more runs in the second inning and conceded fewer extras, this could have been difficult for the hosts.

Australia won a really good toss and decided to bowl first on what looked like a green track meant to aid the bowlers. The ball was nipping around right through the Test match and South Africa had very little joy early in their first inning. They lost four wickets early and a 98-run partnership between Temba Bavuma and Kyle Verreynne helped them cross the 100-run mark. The dismissal of Temba Bavuma triggered another collapse and despite Kyle Verreynne scoring a fighting 64, the visitors managed to put just 152 runs on the board. Mitchell Starc and Nathan Lyon claimed three wickets each with Scott Boland and Pat Cummins chipping in with two each. Australia did not start their first inning on the front foot either losing three wickets early but a 117-run partnership between Steven Smith and Travis Head put them ahead in the game. Travis Head scored 92 runs in 96 deliveries which was a game-changing inning in the context of this game. Kagiso Rabada was the pick of the bowlers taking four wickets in the first inning and Marco Jansen was good as well claiming three scalps.

A comprehensive win for the number one Test side in the world! They have absolutely demolished the South African side but have had massive help from the green wicket. It has been a bowler’s paradise as 34 wickets have fallen over two days and this would not be an ideal Test wicket as there was very little competition between the bat and the ball. Australia had a small target of 34 to chase and they struggled as they lost their openers early. The dismissal of Steven Smith and Travis Head soon after had the Proteas interested but they conceded 19 extras to help Australia take a 1-0 lead in the series.

FIVE WIDES! So the winning runs come as extras. Well it does not matter how the runs come. A sharp bouncer, on middle. Cameron Green ducks under it. The ball flies over the keeper and races away to the fine leg fence. The umpire signals a wide as well due to height. Australia win the match by 6 wickets.
Length ball, on off. Marnus Labuschagne taps it to covers and scampers across for a quick single.
Goes very full, on off. Marnus Labuschagne drives it down the ground. He hits the stumps at the other end though.
This is left alone by Marnus Labuschagne as it is wide of off.
Length, around off, defended out.
This is on a good length, outside off, shapes away a bit. Marnus Labuschagne tries to block it away but gets beaten on the outside edge.

FIVE WIDES! No extras can be afforded when the target is so low. Anrich Nortje bends his back hard and serves a sharp bouncer, on top of off. Marnus Labuschagne ducks under. It is also too high for the keeper. It races away to the fine leg fence, while the umpire signals a wide for height. Just 5 runs needed now and extras have been the top-scorer so far in this inning.
It is very full, on middle and leg. Green tucks it to the man at short leg. South Africa do believe something now, although Australia only need 10 runs to get over the line.
A length ball, on off. Green blocks it to point.
Cameron Green comes in at number 6.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Kagiso Rabada is on fire here and has his fourth wicket! This time it is the top scorer of this game Travis Head who has to depart. He bowls this back of a length and straying down leg side. Travis Head looks to tuck this away fine but gets a faint edge that goes through to the keeper. Kyle Verreynne goes to his right and collects this well. A massive appeal from the players and the umpire raises his finger. Travis Head looks distraught but has to make the long way back to the shed.
Commentary.Howout: c Kyle Verreynne b Kagiso Rabada

Commentary.Commentary: FIVE WIDES! Kagiso Rabada bangs this short to welcome the new batter and Travis Head ducks under this one. The ball keeps rising and goes over the outstretched arm of Kyle Verreynne for four extra runs. The umpire calls this one wide as well and Australia need just 10 more now.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Steven Smith departs and South Africa are still not giving up! Kagiso Rabada bangs this in short and wide outside off, Steven Smith slashes at this one as well and gets an outside edge that flies to the keeper. Kyle Verreynne makes no mistake behind the wicket and Australia are three down now. The South African look umped up and we wonder what would have been had they been defending close to a 100.
Commentary.Howout: c Kyle Verreynne b Kagiso Rabada

Commentary.Commentary: FOUR! That has been carved away to the fence! Kagiso Rabada bowls this one back of a length and outside off. Steven Smith cuts this beautifully towards deep point for a lovely boundary. Just 15 more runs needed.
Kagiso Rabada bowls this back of a length and outside off. Steven Smith raises his arms and lets the ball go through to the keeper.
Length and on off, Marnus Labuschagne defends it out watchfully.
This is a length ball that comes in from outside off. Marnus Labuschagne tries to flick it on his back foot but gets an outside edge as it goes to point.
Length and on off. Marnus Labuschagne gets behind and defends it out.
Goes full, on middle. Marnus Labuschagne flicks it to mid on.
FOUR! Exceptional shot. It is fuller, on middle and leg. Marnus Labuschagne punches it down the ground with straight bat. It goes past mid off and races away.
Shorter, in the channel of uncertainty. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone for the keeper.
A bit fuller, on off. Steven Smith lofts it over mid off on the up. The ball lands safely and the batters take a couple.
Shorter, outside off. Steven Smith leaves it alone.
Steven Smith makes his way out to the middle.

OUT! CAUGHT IN SLIPS! David Warner has to walk back for just three runs. He has been unable to break his shackles in this first Test match. It is a length ball, on off, angling across a bit. David Warner tries to block it on his front foot but only finds a thick outside edge. Sarel Erwee from third slip dives to his right and pouches it with both hands.
Commentary.Howout: c Sarel Erwee b Kagiso Rabada

Commentary.Commentary: Good length, on top of off, moving away. David Warner square up a bit as he defends it to cover.
A length ball, on top of off. David Warner hangs back and taps it to covers.
A short ball, in the corridor of uncertainty. It flies off the deck. David Warner leaves it alone.
Just a single off the over then. Anrich Nortje serves a length ball, wide of off. Marnus Labuschagne shuffles and blocks it in front of him on the off side.
Good leave! It is a short ball, on fifth stump. Marnus Labuschagne shoulders his arms at it.
A sharp bouncer, in the channel. Marnus Labuschagne has a smile on his face as he sways away from the line.
Anrich Nortje serves a length ball, angling in on off. Marnus Labuschagne stays back and defends it with full face of the blade.
Good length, on fifth stump. Marnus Labuschagne shuffles and blocks it out.
A length ball, on middle. Warner gets it to the leg side and crosses.
Marnus Labuschagne makes his way out to the middle at number 3.

OUT! CAUGHT! Usman Khawaja tries to make room and find the gap besides backward point but holes out instead. Kagiso Rabada strike first this time. It is a short ball, around off. Usman Khawaja moves back and goes for the cut shot. He doesn't get through with it and hits it to the right of the fielder at backward point. Keshav Maharaj there takes a sharp catch. Can South Africa build on the early wicket?
Commentary.Howout: c Keshav Maharaj b Kagiso Rabada

Commentary.Commentary: It is a short ball, on middle and leg, climbing onto the batter. Usman Khawaja goes back and pulls it over square leg. The batters take a couple.
On off, pushed to mid off.
Bowls this on a good length and just outside off. Usman Khawaja looks to block but gets beaten and hit on the pads.
Bowls this one slightly full and angled into the stumps. Usman Khawaja clips this towards mid-wicket.
Kagiso Rabada starts the over with a vicious delivery bowled back of a length and just outside off. Usman Khawaja looks to block but is early into his shot and the ball hits the handle of his bat.
FOUR BYES! Misses everyone! It is a sharp bouncer, down the leg side. David Warner leaves it alone. Although it is too high for the keeper as well. It races away to the fine leg fence.
A length ball, on the pads, Warner closes the face of the bat and helps it towards mid-wicket with soft hands.
Anrich Nortje serves it full, shaping across the left-hander. David Warner keeps his bat to himself.
Australia and David Warner are off the mark here. Back of a length, on middle and leg. David Warner hangs back and pulls it down to deep square leg. They take two runs.
A bit shorter, on the bodyline. Warner goes back and tucks it to the man at short leg.
Anrich Nortje steams in from the other end with the new ball. He serves it on a length, on off. Warner opens the face and guides it to point. No run though.
Kagiso Rabada starts his spell with a maiden. This is a length ball, on top of off. It flies off the deck. Usman Khawaja hangs back and creates way for the ball by lifting his blade.
Fifth dot now! Outside off, shaping away. Usman Khawaja has no shot to offer.
Goes full and on off. Usman Khawaja gets his blade down in time to defend it out.
Make that three now! This is shorter, around off, closer to the body this time. Usman Khawaja reads it well and shoulders his arms at it.
Two dots in a row! Rabada goes short, angling away from the left-hander. Usman Khawaja lets it be.
A dot to start with! Kagiso Rabada starts with a length ball, on middle and leg. Usman Khawaja nudges it to short leg.
